140 ShouldThrow GetShouldThrow(Isolate* isolate, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
141  if (should_throw.IsJust()) return should_throw.FromJust();
142 
143  LanguageMode mode = isolate->context()->scope_info()->language_mode();
144  if (mode == LanguageMode::kStrict) return kThrowOnError;
145 
146  for (StackFrameIterator it(isolate, isolate->thread_local_top()); !it.done();
147  it.Advance()) {
148  if (!it.frame()->is_javascript()) continue;
149 
150  // Get the language mode from closure.
151  JavaScriptFrame* js_frame = static_cast<JavaScriptFrame*>(it.frame());
152  std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>> functions;
153  js_frame->GetFunctions(&functions);
154  LanguageMode closure_language_mode = functions.back()->language_mode();
155  if (closure_language_mode > mode) {
156  mode = closure_language_mode;
157  }
158  break;
159  }
160 
161  return is_sloppy(mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
162 }
163 
164 bool ComparisonResultToBool(Operation op, ComparisonResult result) {
165  switch (op) {
166  case Operation::kLessThan:
167  return result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
168  case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
169  return result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan ||
170  result == ComparisonResult::kEqual;
171  case Operation::kGreaterThan:
172  return result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
173  case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
174  return result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan ||
175  result == ComparisonResult::kEqual;
176  default:
177  break;
178  }
179  UNREACHABLE();
180 }
181 
182 std::string ToString(InstanceType instance_type) {
183  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type)) {
184  std::stringstream ss;
185  ss << "[api object] "
186  << static_cast<int16_t>(instance_type) -
187  i::Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType;
188  return ss.str();
189  }
190  switch (instance_type) {
191 #define WRITE_TYPE(TYPE) \
192  case TYPE: \
193  return #TYPE;
194  INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(WRITE_TYPE)
195 #undef WRITE_TYPE
196  }
197 
198  std::stringstream ss;
199  ss << "[unknown instance type " << static_cast<int16_t>(instance_type) << "]";
200  return ss.str();
201 }
202 
203 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, InstanceType instance_type) {
204  return os << ToString(instance_type);
205 }

207 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, PropertyCellType type) {
208  switch (type) {
209  case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
210  return os << "Undefined";
211  case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
212  return os << "Constant";
213  case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
214  return os << "ConstantType";
215  case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
216  return os << "Mutable";
217  case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
218  return os << "InTransition";
219  }
220  UNREACHABLE();
221 }

223 // static
224 DirectHandle<FieldType> Object::OptimalType(Tagged<Object> obj,
225  Isolate* isolate,
226  Representation representation) {
227  if (representation.IsNone()) return FieldType::None(isolate);
228  if (v8_flags.track_field_types) {
229  if (representation.IsHeapObject() && IsHeapObject(obj)) {
230  // We can track only JavaScript objects with stable maps.
231  DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<HeapObject>(obj)->map(), isolate);
232  if (map->is_stable() && IsJSReceiverMap(*map)) {
233  return FieldType::Class(map, isolate);
234  }
235  }
236  }
237  return FieldType::Any(isolate);
238 }
239 
240 Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> Object::NewStorageFor(
241  Isolate* isolate, Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> object,
242  Representation representation) {
243  if (!representation.IsDouble()) return object;
244  Handle<HeapNumber> result = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
245  if (IsUninitialized(*object, isolate)) {
246  result->set_value_as_bits(kHoleNanInt64);
247  } else if (IsHeapNumber(*object)) {
248  // Ensure that all bits of the double value are preserved.
249  result->set_value_as_bits(Cast<HeapNumber>(*object)->value_as_bits());
250  } else {
251  result->set_value(Cast<Smi>(*object).value());
252  }
253  return result;
254 }
255 
256 template <AllocationType allocation_type, typename IsolateT>
257 Handle<JSAny> Object::WrapForRead(IsolateT* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object,
258  Representation representation) {
259  DCHECK(!IsUninitialized(*object, isolate));
260  if (!representation.IsDouble()) {
261  DCHECK(Object::FitsRepresentation(*object, representation));
262  return object;
263  }
264  return isolate->factory()->template NewHeapNumberFromBits<allocation_type>(
265  Cast<HeapNumber>(*object)->value_as_bits());
266 }

271  LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object, Representation representation);

273 MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> Object::ToObjectImpl(Isolate* isolate,
274  DirectHandle<Object> object,
275  const char* method_name) {
276  DCHECK(!IsJSReceiver(*object)); // Use ToObject() for fast path.
277  DirectHandle<Context> native_context = isolate->native_context();
278  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor;
279  if (IsSmi(*object)) {
280  constructor = direct_handle(native_context->number_function(), isolate);
281  } else {
282  int constructor_function_index =
283  Cast<HeapObject>(object)->map()->GetConstructorFunctionIndex();
284  if (constructor_function_index == Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex) {
285  if (method_name != nullptr) {
286  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
287  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNullOrUndefined,
288  isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
289  method_name)));
290  }
291  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
292  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kUndefinedOrNullToObject));
293  }
294  constructor = direct_handle(
295  Cast<JSFunction>(native_context->GetNoCell(constructor_function_index)),
296  isolate);
297  }
298  Handle<JSObject> result = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(constructor);
299  Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(result)->set_value(Cast<JSAny>(*object));
300  return result;
301 }
302 
303 // ES6 section 9.2.1.2, OrdinaryCallBindThis for sloppy callee.
304 // static
305 MaybeDirectHandle<JSReceiver> Object::ConvertReceiver(
306  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
307  if (IsJSReceiver(*object)) return Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
308  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate)) {
309  return isolate->global_proxy();
310  }
311  return Object::ToObject(isolate, object);
312 }

314 // static

316 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
317  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
318 typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToNumber(
319  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
320  while (true) {
321  if (IsNumber(*input)) {
322  return Cast<Number>(input);
323  }
324  if (IsString(*input)) {
325  return String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(input));
326  }
327  if (IsOddball(*input)) {
328  return Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(input));
329  }
330  if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
331  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToNumber));
332  }
333  if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
334  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kBigIntToNumber));
335  }
336  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
337  isolate, input,
338  JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
339  ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber));
340  }
341 }

348 // static
349 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
350  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
351 typename HandleType<Numeric>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToNumeric(
352  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
353  while (true) {
354  if (IsNumber(*input)) {
355  return Cast<Number>(input);
356  }
357  if (IsString(*input)) {
358  return String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(input));
359  }
360  if (IsOddball(*input)) {
361  return Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(input));
362  }
363  if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
364  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToNumber));
365  }
366  if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
367  return Cast<BigInt>(input);
368  }
369  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
370  isolate, input,
371  JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
372  ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber));
373  }
374 }

382 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
383  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
384 typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToInteger(
385  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
386  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ConvertToNumber(isolate, input));
387  if (IsSmi(*input)) return Cast<Smi>(input);
388  return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
389  DoubleToInteger(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value()));
390 }

415  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
416 typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToUint32(
417  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
418  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ConvertToNumber(isolate, input));

423  DoubleToUint32(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value()));

448 // ES6 7.1.14
449 // static
450 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
451  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
452 typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToPropertyKey(
453  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> value) {
454  // 1. Let key be ToPrimitive(argument, hint String).
455  typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType maybe_key =
456  Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, value, ToPrimitiveHint::kString);
457  // 2. ReturnIfAbrupt(key).
458  HandleType<Object> key;
459  if (!maybe_key.ToHandle(&key)) return key;
460  // 3. If Type(key) is Symbol, then return key.
461  if (IsSymbol(*key)) return key;
462  // 4. Return ToString(key).
463  // Extending spec'ed behavior, we'd be happy to return an element index.
464  if (IsSmi(*key)) return key;
465  if (IsHeapNumber(*key)) {
466  uint32_t uint_value;
467  if (Object::ToArrayLength(*value, &uint_value) &&
468  uint_value <= static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::kMaxValue)) {
469  return HandleType<Object>(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(uint_value)),
470  isolate);
471  }
472  }
473  return Object::ToString(isolate, key);
474 }

477 Object::ConvertToPropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> input);

479 Object::ConvertToPropertyKey(Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<Object> input);

481 // static
482 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
483  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
484 typename HandleType<String>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToString(
485  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
486  while (true) {
487  if (IsOddball(*input)) {
488  HandleType<String> result(Cast<Oddball>(input)->to_string(), isolate);
489  return result;
490  }
491  if (IsNumber(*input)) {
492  return isolate->factory()->NumberToString(input);
493  }
494  if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
495  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToString));
496  }
497  if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
498  return BigInt::ToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(input));
499  }
500 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
501  // We generally don't let the WasmNull escape into the JavaScript world,
502  // but some builtins may encounter it when called directly from Wasm code.
503  if (IsWasmNull(*input)) {
504  return isolate->factory()->null_string();
505  }
506 #endif
507  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
508  isolate, input,
509  JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
510  ToPrimitiveHint::kString));
511  // The previous isString() check happened in Object::ToString and thus we
512  // put it at the end of the loop in this helper.
513  if (IsString(*input)) {
514  return Cast<String>(input);
515  }
516  }
517 }

522  Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<Object> input);

526 bool IsErrorObject(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
527  if (!IsJSObject(*object)) return false;
528  return ErrorUtils::HasErrorStackSymbolOwnProperty(isolate,
529  Cast<JSObject>(object));
530 }
531 
532 DirectHandle<String> AsStringOrEmpty(Isolate* isolate,
533  DirectHandle<Object> object) {
534  return IsString(*object) ? Cast<String>(object)
535  : isolate->factory()->empty_string();
536 }
537 
538 DirectHandle<String> NoSideEffectsErrorToString(
539  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> error) {
540  DirectHandle<Name> name_key = isolate->factory()->name_string();
541  DirectHandle<Object> name =
542  JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, name_key);
543  DirectHandle<String> name_str = AsStringOrEmpty(isolate, name);
544 
545  DirectHandle<Name> msg_key = isolate->factory()->message_string();
546  DirectHandle<Object> msg =
547  JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, msg_key);
548  DirectHandle<String> msg_str = AsStringOrEmpty(isolate, msg);
549 
550  if (name_str->length() == 0) return msg_str;
551  if (msg_str->length() == 0) return name_str;
552 
553  constexpr const char error_suffix[] = "<a very large string>";
554  constexpr uint32_t error_suffix_size = sizeof(error_suffix);
555  uint32_t suffix_size = std::min(error_suffix_size, msg_str->length());
556 
557  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
558  if (name_str->length() + suffix_size + 2 /* ": " */ > String::kMaxLength) {
559  constexpr const char connector[] = "... : ";
560  int connector_size = sizeof(connector);
561  DirectHandle<String> truncated_name =
562  isolate->factory()->NewProperSubString(
563  name_str, 0,
564  name_str->length() - error_suffix_size - connector_size);
565  builder.AppendString(truncated_name);
566  builder.AppendCStringLiteral(connector);
567  builder.AppendCStringLiteral(error_suffix);
568  } else {
569  builder.AppendString(name_str);
570  builder.AppendCStringLiteral(": ");
571  if (builder.Length() + msg_str->length() <= String::kMaxLength) {
572  builder.AppendString(msg_str);
573  } else {
574  builder.AppendCStringLiteral(error_suffix);
575  }
576  }
577 
578  return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
579 }
580 
581 } // namespace
582 
583 // static
584 MaybeDirectHandle<String> Object::NoSideEffectsToMaybeString(
585  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> input) {
586  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
587 
588  if (IsString(*input) || IsNumber(*input) || IsOddball(*input)) {
589  return Object::ToString(isolate, input).ToHandleChecked();
590  } else if (IsJSProxy(*input)) {
591  DirectHandle<Object> currInput = input;
592  do {
593  Tagged<HeapObject> target = Cast<JSProxy>(currInput)->target(isolate);
594  currInput = direct_handle(target, isolate);
595  } while (IsJSProxy(*currInput));
596  return NoSideEffectsToString(isolate, currInput);
597  } else if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
598  return BigInt::NoSideEffectsToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(input));
599  } else if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*input)) {
600  // -- F u n c t i o n
601  DirectHandle<String> fun_str;
602  if (IsJSBoundFunction(*input)) {
603  fun_str =
604  JSBoundFunction::ToString(isolate, Cast<JSBoundFunction>(input));
605  } else if (IsJSWrappedFunction(*input)) {
606  fun_str =
607  JSWrappedFunction::ToString(isolate, Cast<JSWrappedFunction>(input));
608  } else {
609  DCHECK(IsJSFunction(*input));
610  fun_str = JSFunction::ToString(isolate, Cast<JSFunction>(input));
611  }
612 
613  if (fun_str->length() > 128) {
614  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
615  builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(fun_str, 0, 111));
616  builder.AppendCStringLiteral("...<omitted>...");
617  builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
618  fun_str, fun_str->length() - 2, fun_str->length()));
619 
620  return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
621  }
622  return fun_str;
623  } else if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
624  // -- S y m b o l
625  DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(input);
626 
627  if (symbol->is_private_name()) {
628  return DirectHandle<String>(Cast<String>(symbol->description()), isolate);
629  }
630 
631  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
632  builder.AppendCStringLiteral("Symbol(");
633  if (IsString(symbol->description())) {
634  DirectHandle<String> description(Cast<String>(symbol->description()),
635  isolate);
636  if (description->length() > 128) {
637  builder.AppendString(
638  isolate->factory()->NewSubString(description, 0, 56));
639  builder.AppendCStringLiteral("...<omitted>...");
640  builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
641  description, description->length() - 56, description->length()));
642  } else {
643  builder.AppendString(description);
644  }
645  }
646  builder.AppendCharacter(')');
647 
648  return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
649  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*input)) {
650  // -- J S R e c e i v e r
651  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(input);
652  DirectHandle<Object> to_string = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
653  isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->toString_string());
654 
655  if (IsErrorObject(isolate, input) ||
656  *to_string == *isolate->error_to_string()) {
657  // When internally formatting error objects, use a side-effects-free
658  // version of Error.prototype.toString independent of the actually
659  // installed toString method.
660  return NoSideEffectsErrorToString(isolate, receiver);
661  } else if (*to_string == *isolate->object_to_string()) {
662  DirectHandle<Object> ctor = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
663  isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->constructor_string());
664  if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*ctor)) {
665  DirectHandle<String> ctor_name;
666  if (IsJSBoundFunction(*ctor)) {
667  ctor_name =
668  JSBoundFunction::GetName(isolate, Cast<JSBoundFunction>(ctor))
669  .ToHandleChecked();
670  } else if (IsJSFunction(*ctor)) {
671  ctor_name = JSFunction::GetName(isolate, Cast<JSFunction>(ctor));
672  }
673 
674  if (ctor_name->length() != 0) {
675  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
676  builder.AppendCStringLiteral("#<");
677  builder.AppendString(ctor_name);
678  builder.AppendCharacter('>');
679 
680  return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
681  }
682  }
683  }
684  }
685  return {};
686 }
687 
688 // static
689 DirectHandle<String> Object::NoSideEffectsToString(Isolate* isolate,
690  DirectHandle<Object> input) {
691  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
692 
693  // Try to convert input to a meaningful string.
694  MaybeDirectHandle<String> maybe_string =
695  NoSideEffectsToMaybeString(isolate, input);
696  DirectHandle<String> string_handle;
697  if (maybe_string.ToHandle(&string_handle)) {
698  return string_handle;
699  }
700 
701  // At this point, input is either none of the above or a JSReceiver.
702 
703  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver;
704  if (IsJSReceiver(*input)) {
705  receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(input);
706  } else {
707  // This is the only case where Object::ToObject throws.
708  DCHECK(!IsSmi(*input));
709  int constructor_function_index =
710  Cast<HeapObject>(input)->map()->GetConstructorFunctionIndex();
711  if (constructor_function_index == Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex) {
712  return isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked("[object Unknown]");
713  }
714 
715  receiver = Object::ToObjectImpl(isolate, input).ToHandleChecked();
716  }
717 
718  DirectHandle<String> builtin_tag =
719  direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate);
720  DirectHandle<Object> tag_obj = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
721  isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->to_string_tag_symbol());
722  DirectHandle<String> tag =
723  IsString(*tag_obj) ? Cast<String>(tag_obj) : builtin_tag;
724 
725  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
726  builder.AppendCStringLiteral("[object ");
727  builder.AppendString(tag);
728  builder.AppendCharacter(']');
729 
730  return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
731 }
732 
733 // static
734 MaybeHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToLength(Isolate* isolate,
735  DirectHandle<Object> input) {
736  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ToNumber(isolate, input));
737  if (IsSmi(*input)) {
738  int value = std::max(Smi::ToInt(*input), 0);
739  return handle(Smi::FromInt(value), isolate);
740  }
741  double len = DoubleToInteger(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value());
742  if (len <= 0.0) {
743  return handle(Smi::zero(), isolate);
744  } else if (len >= kMaxSafeInteger) {
745  len = kMaxSafeInteger;
746  }
747  return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(len);
748 }
749 
750 // static
751 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
752  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
753 typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToIndex(
754  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input, MessageTemplate error_index) {
755  if (IsUndefined(*input, isolate))
756  return HandleType<Number>(Smi::zero(), isolate);
757  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ToNumber(isolate, input));
758  if (IsSmi(*input) && Smi::ToInt(*input) >= 0) return Cast<Smi>(input);
759  double len = DoubleToInteger(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*input)));
760  HandleType<Number> js_len = isolate->factory()->NewNumber(len);
761  if (len < 0.0 || len > kMaxSafeInteger) {
762  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewRangeError(error_index, js_len));
763  }
764  return js_len;
765 }

767 template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeDirectHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToIndex(
768  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> input, MessageTemplate error_index);
769 template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeIndirectHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToIndex(
770  Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<Object> input,
771  MessageTemplate error_index);

773 template <typename IsolateT>
774 // static
775 bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object> obj, IsolateT* isolate) {
776  if (IsSmi(obj)) return Smi::ToInt(obj) != 0;
777  DCHECK(IsHeapObject(obj));
778  if (IsBoolean(obj)) return IsTrue(obj, isolate);
779  if (IsNullOrUndefined(obj, isolate)) return false;
780 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
781  if (IsWasmNull(obj)) return false;
782 #endif
783  if (IsUndetectable(obj)) return false; // Undetectable object is false.
784  if (IsString(obj)) return Cast<String>(obj)->length() != 0;
785  if (IsHeapNumber(obj)) return DoubleToBoolean(Cast<HeapNumber>(obj)->value());
786  if (IsBigInt(obj)) return Cast<BigInt>(obj)->ToBoolean();
787  return true;
788 }
789 template bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object>, Isolate*);
790 template bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object>, LocalIsolate*);
791 
792 // static
793 Tagged<Object> Object::ToBoolean(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
794  if (IsBoolean(obj)) return obj;
795  return isolate->heap()->ToBoolean(Object::BooleanValue(obj, isolate));
796 }

798 namespace {

800 // TODO(bmeurer): Maybe we should introduce a marker interface Number,
801 // where we put all these methods at some point?
802 ComparisonResult StrictNumberCompare(double x, double y) {
803  if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) {
804  return ComparisonResult::kUndefined;
805  } else if (x < y) {
806  return ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
807  } else if (x > y) {
808  return ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
809  } else {
810  return ComparisonResult::kEqual;
811  }
812 }
813 
814 // See Number case of ES6#sec-strict-equality-comparison
815 // Returns false if x or y is NaN, treats -0.0 as equal to 0.0.
816 bool StrictNumberEquals(double x, double y) {
817  // Must check explicitly for NaN's on Windows, but -0 works fine.
818  if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) return false;
819  return x == y;
820 }
821 
822 bool StrictNumberEquals(const Tagged<Number> x, const Tagged<Number> y) {
823  return StrictNumberEquals(Object::NumberValue(x), Object::NumberValue(y));
824 }
825 
826 bool StrictNumberEquals(DirectHandle<Number> x, DirectHandle<Number> y) {
827  return StrictNumberEquals(*x, *y);
828 }
829 
830 ComparisonResult Reverse(ComparisonResult result) {
831  if (result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan) {
832  return ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
833  }
834  if (result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan) {
835  return ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
836  }
837  return result;
838 }
839 
840 } // anonymous namespace
841 
842 // static
843 Maybe<ComparisonResult> Object::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
844  DirectHandle<Object> x,
845  DirectHandle<Object> y) {
846  // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 3 and 4.
847  if (!Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, x, ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber).ToHandle(&x) ||
848  !Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, y, ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber).ToHandle(&y)) {
849  return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
850  }
851  if (IsString(*x) && IsString(*y)) {
852  // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 5.
853  return Just(String::Compare(isolate, Cast<String>(x), Cast<String>(y)));
854  }
855  if (IsBigInt(*x) && IsString(*y)) {
856  return BigInt::CompareToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(x), Cast<String>(y));
857  }
858  if (IsString(*x) && IsBigInt(*y)) {
859  Maybe<ComparisonResult> maybe_result =
860  BigInt::CompareToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<String>(x));
861  ComparisonResult result;
862  if (maybe_result.To(&result)) {
863  return Just(Reverse(result));
864  } else {
865  return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
866  }
867  }
868  // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 6.
869  if (!Object::ToNumeric(isolate, x).ToHandle(&x) ||
870  !Object::ToNumeric(isolate, y).ToHandle(&y)) {
871  return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
872  }
873 
874  bool x_is_number = IsNumber(*x);
875  bool y_is_number = IsNumber(*y);
876  if (x_is_number && y_is_number) {
877  return Just(
878  StrictNumberCompare(Object::NumberValue(*x), Object::NumberValue(*y)));
879  } else if (!x_is_number && !y_is_number) {
880  return Just(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(x), Cast<BigInt>(y)));
881  } else if (x_is_number) {
882  return Just(Reverse(BigInt::CompareToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), x)));
883  } else {
884  return Just(BigInt::CompareToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(x), y));
885  }
886 }
887 
888 Maybe<bool> Object::Equals(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> x,
889  DirectHandle<Object> y) {
890  // This is the generic version of Abstract Equality Comparison. Must be in
891  // sync with CodeStubAssembler::Equal.
892  while (true) {
893  if (IsNumber(*x)) {
894  if (IsNumber(*y)) {
895  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x), Cast<Number>(*y)));
896  } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
897  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x),
898  Cast<Oddball>(y)->to_number()));
899  } else if (IsString(*y)) {
900  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(
901  Cast<Number>(x), String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(y))));
902  } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
903  return Just(BigInt::EqualToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<Number>(x)));
904  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
905  if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
906  .ToHandle(&y)) {
907  return Nothing<bool>();
908  }
909  } else {
910  return Just(false);
911  }
912  } else if (IsString(*x)) {
913  if (IsString(*y)) {
914  return Just(String::Equals(isolate, Cast<String>(x), Cast<String>(y)));
915  } else if (IsNumber(*y)) {
916  x = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(x));
917  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x), Cast<Number>(*y)));
918  } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
919  x = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(x));
920  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x),
921  Cast<Oddball>(y)->to_number()));
922  } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
923  return BigInt::EqualToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<String>(x));
924  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
925  if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
926  .ToHandle(&y)) {
927  return Nothing<bool>();
928  }
929  } else {
930  return Just(false);
931  }
932  } else if (IsBoolean(*x)) {
933  if (IsOddball(*y)) {
934  return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
935  } else if (IsNumber(*y)) {
936  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Oddball>(x)->to_number(),
937  Cast<Number>(*y)));
938  } else if (IsString(*y)) {
939  y = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(y));
940  return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Oddball>(x)->to_number(),
941  Cast<Number>(*y)));
942  } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
943  x = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(x));
944  return Just(BigInt::EqualToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), x));
945  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
946  if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
947  .ToHandle(&y)) {
948  return Nothing<bool>();
949  }
950  x = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(x));
951  } else {
952  return Just(false);
953  }
954  } else if (IsSymbol(*x)) {
955  if (IsSymbol(*y)) {
956  return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
957  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
958  if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
959  .ToHandle(&y)) {
960  return Nothing<bool>();
961  }
962  } else {
963  return Just(false);
964  }
965  } else if (IsBigInt(*x)) {
966  if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
967  return Just(BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(*x), Cast<BigInt>(*y)));
968  }
969  return Equals(isolate, y, x);
970  } else if (IsJSReceiver(*x)) {
971  if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
972  return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
973  } else if (IsUndetectable(*y)) {
974  return Just(IsUndetectable(*x));
975  } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
976  y = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(y));
977  } else if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(x))
978  .ToHandle(&x)) {
979  return Nothing<bool>();
980  }
981  } else {
982  return Just(IsUndetectable(*x) && IsUndetectable(*y));
983  }
984  }
985 }
986 
987 // static
988 bool Object::StrictEquals(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> that) {
989  if (IsNumber(obj)) {
990  if (!IsNumber(that)) return false;
991  return StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(obj), Cast<Number>(that));
992  } else if (IsString(obj)) {
993  if (!IsString(that)) return false;
994  return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(that));
995  } else if (IsBigInt(obj)) {
996  if (!IsBigInt(that)) return false;
997  return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(that));
998  }
999  return obj == that;
1000 }
1001 
1002 // static
1003 Handle<String> Object::TypeOf(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
1004  if (IsNumber(*object)) return isolate->factory()->number_string();
1005  if (IsOddball(*object))
1006  return handle(Cast<Oddball>(*object)->type_of(), isolate);
1007  if (IsUndetectable(*object)) {
1008  return isolate->factory()->undefined_string();
1009  }
1010  if (IsString(*object)) return isolate->factory()->string_string();
1011  if (IsSymbol(*object)) return isolate->factory()->symbol_string();
1012  if (IsBigInt(*object)) return isolate->factory()->bigint_string();
1013  if (IsCallable(*object)) return isolate->factory()->function_string();
1014  return isolate->factory()->object_string();
1015 }

1017 // static
1018 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::Add(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> lhs,
1019  Handle<Object> rhs) {
1020  if (IsNumber(*lhs) && IsNumber(*rhs)) {
1021  return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
1022  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*lhs)) +
1023  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*rhs)));
1024  } else if (IsString(*lhs) && IsString(*rhs)) {
1025  return isolate->factory()->NewConsString(Cast<String>(lhs),
1026  Cast<String>(rhs));
1027  }
1028  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs, Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, lhs));
1029  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs, Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, rhs));
1030  if (IsString(*lhs) || IsString(*rhs)) {
1031  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs, Object::ToString(isolate, rhs));
1032  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs, Object::ToString(isolate, lhs));
1033  return isolate->factory()->NewConsString(Cast<String>(lhs),
1034  Cast<String>(rhs));
1035  }
1036  DirectHandle<Number> lhs_number;
1037  DirectHandle<Number> rhs_number;
1038  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs_number,
1039  Object::ToNumber(isolate, rhs));
1040  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs_number,
1041  Object::ToNumber(isolate, lhs));
1042  return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(Object::NumberValue(*lhs_number) +
1043  Object::NumberValue(*rhs_number));
1044 }
1045 
1046 // static
1047 MaybeHandle<Object> Object::OrdinaryHasInstance(Isolate* isolate,
1048  DirectHandle<JSAny> callable,
1049  DirectHandle<JSAny> object) {
1050  // The {callable} must have a [[Call]] internal method.
1051  if (!IsCallable(*callable)) return isolate->factory()->false_value();
1052 
1053  // Check if {callable} is a bound function, and if so retrieve its
1054  // [[BoundTargetFunction]] and use that instead of {callable}.
1055  if (IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) {
1056  // Since there is a mutual recursion here, we might run out of stack
1057  // space for long chains of bound functions.
1058  STACK_CHECK(isolate, MaybeHandle<Object>());
1059  DirectHandle<JSCallable> bound_callable(
1060  Cast<JSBoundFunction>(callable)->bound_target_function(), isolate);
1061  return Object::InstanceOf(isolate, object, bound_callable);
1062  }
1063 
1064  // If {object} is not a receiver, return false.
1065  if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) return isolate->factory()->false_value();
1066 
1067  // Get the "prototype" of {callable}; raise an error if it's not a receiver.
1068  DirectHandle<Object> prototype;
1069  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1070  isolate, prototype,
1071  Object::GetProperty(isolate, callable,
1072  isolate->factory()->prototype_string()));
1073  if (!IsJSReceiver(*prototype)) {
1074  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1075  isolate,
1076  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInstanceofNonobjectProto, prototype));
1077  }
1078 
1079  // Return whether or not {prototype} is in the prototype chain of {object}.
1080  Maybe<bool> result = JSReceiver::HasInPrototypeChain(
1081  isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), prototype);
1082  if (result.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
1083  return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(result.FromJust());
1084 }
1085 
1086 // static
1087 MaybeHandle<Object> Object::InstanceOf(Isolate* isolate,
1088  DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
1089  DirectHandle<JSAny> callable) {
1090  // The {callable} must be a receiver.
1091  if (!IsJSReceiver(*callable)) {
1092  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1093  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectInInstanceOfCheck));
1094  }
1095 
1096  // Lookup the @@hasInstance method on {callable}.
1097  DirectHandle<Object> inst_of_handler;
1098  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1099  isolate, inst_of_handler,
1100  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(callable),
1101  isolate->factory()->has_instance_symbol()));
1102  if (!IsUndefined(*inst_of_handler, isolate)) {
1103  // Call the {inst_of_handler} on the {callable}.
1104  DirectHandle<Object> result;
1105  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {object};
1106  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
1107  Execution::Call(isolate, inst_of_handler,
1108  callable, base::VectorOf(args)));
1109  return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(
1110  Object::BooleanValue(*result, isolate));
1111  }
1112 
1113  // The {callable} must have a [[Call]] internal method.
1114  if (!IsCallable(*callable)) {
1115  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1116  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonCallableInInstanceOfCheck));
1117  }
1118 
1119  // Fall back to OrdinaryHasInstance with {callable} and {object}.
1120  Handle<Object> result;
1121  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1122  isolate, result, Object::OrdinaryHasInstance(isolate, callable, object));
1123  return result;
1124 }
1125 
1126 // static
1127 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::GetMethod(Isolate* isolate,
1128  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
1129  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
1130  Handle<Object> func;
1131  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, func,
1132  JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, receiver, name));
1133  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*func, isolate)) {
1134  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1135  }
1136  if (!IsCallable(*func)) {
1137  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyNotFunction,
1138  func, name, receiver));
1139  }
1140  return func;
1141 }

1143 namespace {
1144 
1145 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> CreateListFromArrayLikeFastPath(
1146  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object, ElementTypes element_types) {
1147  if (element_types == ElementTypes::kAll) {
1148  if (IsJSArray(*object)) {
1149  DirectHandle<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(object);
1150  uint32_t length;
1151  if (!array->HasArrayPrototype(isolate) ||
1152  !Object::ToUint32(array->length(), &length) ||
1153  !array->HasFastElements() ||
1154  !JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *array)) {
1155  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
1156  }
1157  return array->GetElementsAccessor()->CreateListFromArrayLike(
1158  isolate, array, length);
1159  } else if (IsJSTypedArray(*object)) {
1160  DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object);
1161  size_t length = array->GetLength();
1162  if (array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
1163  length > static_cast<size_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength)) {
1164  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
1165  }
1166  static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength <=
1167  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
1168  return array->GetElementsAccessor()->CreateListFromArrayLike(
1169  isolate, array, static_cast<uint32_t>(length));
1170  }
1171  }
1172  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
1173 }
1174 
1175 } // namespace
1176 
1177 // static
1178 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> Object::CreateListFromArrayLike(
1179  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object, ElementTypes element_types) {
1180  // Fast-path for JSArray and JSTypedArray.
1181  MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> fast_result =
1182  CreateListFromArrayLikeFastPath(isolate, object, element_types);
1183  if (!fast_result.is_null()) return fast_result;
1184  // 1. ReturnIfAbrupt(object).
1185  // 2. (default elementTypes -- not applicable.)
1186  // 3. If Type(obj) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1187  if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1188  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1189  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject,
1190  isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
1191  "CreateListFromArrayLike")));
1192  }
1193 
1194  // 4. Let len be ? ToLength(? Get(obj, "length")).
1195  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
1196  DirectHandle<Object> raw_length_number;
1197  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, raw_length_number,
1198  Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(isolate, receiver));
1199  uint32_t len;
1200  if (!Object::ToUint32(*raw_length_number, &len) ||
1201  len > static_cast<uint32_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength)) {
1202  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1203  NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
1204  }
1205  // 5. Let list be an empty List.
1206  DirectHandle<FixedArray> list = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(len);
1207  // 6. Let index be 0.
1208  // 7. Repeat while index < len:
1209  for (uint32_t index = 0; index < len; ++index) {
1210  // 7a. Let indexName be ToString(index).
1211  // 7b. Let next be ? Get(obj, indexName).
1212  DirectHandle<Object> next;
1213  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1214  isolate, next, JSReceiver::GetElement(isolate, receiver, index));
1215  switch (element_types) {
1216  case ElementTypes::kAll:
1217  // Nothing to do.
1218  break;
1219  case ElementTypes::kStringAndSymbol: {
1220  // 7c. If Type(next) is not an element of elementTypes, throw a
1221  // TypeError exception.
1222  if (!IsName(*next)) {
1223  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1224  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNotPropertyName, next));
1225  }
1226  // 7d. Append next as the last element of list.
1227  // Internalize on the fly so we can use pointer identity later.
1228  next = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(Cast<Name>(next));
1229  break;
1230  }
1231  }
1232  list->set(index, *next);
1233  // 7e. Set index to index + 1. (See loop header.)
1234  }
1235  // 8. Return list.
1236  return list;
1237 }
1238 
1239 // static
1240 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(
1241  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
1242  DirectHandle<Object> val;
1243  DirectHandle<Name> key = isolate->factory()->length_string();
1244  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, val,
1245  JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, object, key));
1246  return Object::ToLength(isolate, val);
1247 }
1248 
1249 // static
1250 MaybeHandle<Object> Object::GetProperty(LookupIterator* it,
1251  bool is_global_reference) {
1252  for (;; it->Next()) {
1253  switch (it->state()) {
1254  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1255  UNREACHABLE();
1256  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1257  bool was_found;
1258  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1259  // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by
1260  // the global proxy.
1261  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1262  receiver = direct_handle(
1263  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), it->isolate());
1264  }
1265  if (is_global_reference) {
1266  Maybe<bool> maybe = JSProxy::HasProperty(
1267  it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), it->GetName());
1268  if (maybe.IsNothing()) return {};
1269  if (!maybe.FromJust()) {
1270  it->NotFound();
1271  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1272  }
1273  }
1274  MaybeHandle<JSAny> result =
1275  JSProxy::GetProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1276  it->GetName(), receiver, &was_found);
1277  if (!was_found && !is_global_reference) it->NotFound();
1278  return result;
1279  }
1280  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1281  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
1282  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
1283  bool done;
1284  Handle<JSAny> result;
1285  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1286  it->isolate(), result,
1287  JSObject::GetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, &done));
1288  if (done) return result;
1289  continue;
1290  }
1291  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1292  if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
1293  return JSObject::GetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
1294  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1295  return GetPropertyWithAccessor(it);
1296  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1297  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1298  case LookupIterator::DATA:
1299  return it->GetDataValue();
1300  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1301  return it->GetStringPropertyValue();
1302  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1303  if (it->IsPrivateName()) {
1304  auto private_symbol = Cast<Symbol>(it->name());
1305  DirectHandle<String> name_string(
1306  Cast<String>(private_symbol->description()), it->isolate());
1307  if (private_symbol->is_private_brand()) {
1308  DirectHandle<String> class_name =
1309  name_string->length() == 0
1310  ? it->isolate()->factory()->anonymous_string()
1311  : name_string;
1312  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1313  it->isolate(),
1314  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandInstance,
1315  class_name));
1316  }
1317  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1318  it->isolate(),
1319  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMemberRead,
1320  name_string));
1321  }
1322 
1323  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1324  }
1325  UNREACHABLE();
1326  }
1327 }
1328 
1329 // static
1330 MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSProxy::GetProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1331  DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
1332  DirectHandle<Name> name,
1333  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
1334  bool* was_found) {
1335  *was_found = true;
1336 
1337  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
1338  STACK_CHECK(isolate, kNullMaybeHandle);
1339  DirectHandle<Name> trap_name = isolate->factory()->get_string();
1340  // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true.
1341  // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
1342  DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSReceiver, Null>> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
1343  // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
1344  // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
1345  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
1346  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1347  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
1348  }
1349  // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
1350  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
1351  // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "get").
1352  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
1353  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1354  isolate, trap,
1355  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name));
1356  // 7. If trap is undefined, then
1357  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
1358  // 7.a Return target.[[Get]](P, Receiver).
1359  PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
1360  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, key, target);
1361  MaybeHandle<JSAny> result = Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(&it));
1362  *was_found = it.IsFound();
1363  return result;
1364  }
1365  // 8. Let trapResult be ? Call(trap, handler, target, P, Receiver).
1366  Handle<Object> trap_result;
1367  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name, receiver};
1368  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1369  isolate, trap_result,
1370  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)));
1371 
1372  MaybeHandle<JSAny> result =
1373  JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(isolate, name, target, trap_result, kGet);
1374  if (result.is_null()) {
1375  return result;
1376  }
1377 
1378  // 11. Return trap_result
1379  return Cast<JSAny>(trap_result);
1380 }
1381 
1382 // static
1383 MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(
1384  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
1385  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result, AccessKind access_kind) {
1386  // 9. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
1387  PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
1388  Maybe<bool> target_found =
1389  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
1390  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(target_found);
1391  // 10. If targetDesc is not undefined, then
1392  if (target_found.FromJust()) {
1393  // 10.a. If IsDataDescriptor(targetDesc) and targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
1394  // false and targetDesc.[[Writable]] is false, then
1395  // 10.a.i. If SameValue(trapResult, targetDesc.[[Value]]) is false,
1396  // throw a TypeError exception.
1397  bool inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1398  !target_desc.configurable() &&
1399  !target_desc.writable() &&
1400  !Object::SameValue(*trap_result, *target_desc.value());
1401  if (inconsistent) {
1402  if (access_kind == kGet) {
1403  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1404  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetNonConfigurableData,
1405  name, target_desc.value(), trap_result));
1406  } else {
1407  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
1408  MessageTemplate::kProxySetFrozenData, name));
1409  return {};
1410  }
1411  }
1412  // 10.b. If IsAccessorDescriptor(targetDesc) and targetDesc.[[Configurable]]
1413  // is false and targetDesc.[[Get]] is undefined, then
1414  // 10.b.i. If trapResult is not undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
1415  if (access_kind == kGet) {
1416  inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1417  !target_desc.configurable() &&
1418  IsUndefined(*target_desc.get(), isolate) &&
1419  !IsUndefined(*trap_result, isolate);
1420  } else {
1421  inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1422  !target_desc.configurable() &&
1423  IsUndefined(*target_desc.set(), isolate);
1424  }
1425  if (inconsistent) {
1426  if (access_kind == kGet) {
1427  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1428  isolate,
1429  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetNonConfigurableAccessor,
1430  name, trap_result));
1431  } else {
1432  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
1433  MessageTemplate::kProxySetFrozenAccessor, name));
1434  return {};
1435  }
1436  }
1437  }
1438  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1439 }
1440 
1441 // static
1442 bool Object::ToInt32(Tagged<Object> obj, int32_t* value) {
1443  if (IsSmi(obj)) {
1444  *value = Smi::ToInt(obj);
1445  return true;
1446  }
1447  if (IsHeapNumber(obj)) {
1448  double num = Cast<HeapNumber>(obj)->value();
1449  // Check range before conversion to avoid undefined behavior.
1450  if (num >= kMinInt && num <= kMaxInt && FastI2D(FastD2I(num)) == num) {
1451  *value = FastD2I(num);
1452  return true;
1453  }
1454  }
1455  return false;
1456 }
1457 
1458 // ES6 9.5.1
1459 // static
1460 MaybeDirectHandle<JSPrototype> JSProxy::GetPrototype(
1461  DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
1462  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
1463  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = isolate->factory()->getPrototypeOf_string();
1464 
1465  STACK_CHECK(isolate, {});
1466 
1467  // 1. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot.
1468  // 2. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
1469  // 3. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
1470  // 4. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot.
1471  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
1472  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1473  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
1474  }
1475  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
1476  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
1477 
1478  // 5. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getPrototypeOf").
1479  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
1480  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, trap,
1481  Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name));
1482  // 6. If trap is undefined, then return target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
1483  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
1484  return JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target);
1485  }
1486  // 7. Let handlerProto be ? Call(trap, handler, target).
1487  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
1488  DirectHandle<Object> handler_proto_result;
1489  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1490  isolate, handler_proto_result,
1491  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)));
1492  // 8. If Type(handlerProto) is neither Object nor Null, throw a TypeError.
1493  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> handler_proto;
1494  if (!TryCast(handler_proto_result, &handler_proto)) {
1495  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1496  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetPrototypeOfInvalid));
1497  }
1498  // 9. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
1499  Maybe<bool> is_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
1500  MAYBE_RETURN(is_extensible, {});
1501  // 10. If extensibleTarget is true, return handlerProto.
1502  if (is_extensible.FromJust()) return handler_proto;
1503  // 11. Let targetProto be ? target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
1504  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> target_proto;
1505  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, target_proto,
1506  JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target));
1507  // 12. If SameValue(handlerProto, targetProto) is false, throw a TypeError.
1508  if (!Object::SameValue(*handler_proto, *target_proto)) {
1509  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1510  isolate,
1511  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetPrototypeOfNonExtensible));
1512  }
1513  // 13. Return handlerProto.
1514  return handler_proto;
1515 }
1516 
1517 MaybeHandle<JSAny> Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(LookupIterator* it) {
1518  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1519  DirectHandle<Object> structure = it->GetAccessors();
1520  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1521  // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by the
1522  // global proxy.
1523  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1524  receiver =
1525  direct_handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), isolate);
1526  }
1527 
1528  // We should never get here to initialize a const with the hole value since a
1529  // const declaration would conflict with the getter.
1530  DCHECK(!IsForeign(*structure));
1531 
1532  // API style callbacks.
1533  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1534  if (IsAccessorInfo(*structure)) {
1535  DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
1536  auto info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(structure);
1537 
1538  if (!info->has_getter(isolate)) {
1539  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1540  }
1541 
1542  if (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1543  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, receiver,
1544  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver));
1545  }
1546 
1547  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, info->data(), *receiver, *holder,
1548  Just(kDontThrow));
1549  DirectHandle<JSAny> result = args.CallAccessorGetter(info, name);
1550  RETURN_EXCEPTION_IF_EXCEPTION(isolate);
1551  Handle<JSAny> reboxed_result(*result, isolate);
1552  if (info->replace_on_access() && IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1553  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate,
1554  Accessors::ReplaceAccessorWithDataProperty(
1555  isolate, receiver, holder, name, result));
1556  }
1557  return reboxed_result;
1558  }
1559 
1560  auto accessor_pair = Cast<AccessorPair>(structure);
1561  // AccessorPair with 'cached' private property.
1562  if (it->TryLookupCachedProperty(accessor_pair)) {
1563  return Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(it));
1564  }
1565 
1566  // Regular accessor.
1567  DirectHandle<Object> getter(accessor_pair->getter(), isolate);
1568  if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
1569  SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate, holder->GetCreationContext().value());
1570  return Cast<JSAny>(Builtins::InvokeApiFunction(
1571  isolate, false, Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(getter), receiver, {},
1572  isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1573  } else if (IsCallable(*getter)) {
1574  // TODO(rossberg): nicer would be to cast to some JSCallable here...
1575  return Object::GetPropertyWithDefinedGetter(receiver,
1576  Cast<JSReceiver>(getter));
1577  }
1578  // Getter is not a function.
1579  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1580 }
1581 
1582 Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(
1583  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1584  Maybe<ShouldThrow> maybe_should_throw) {
1585  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1586  DirectHandle<Object> structure = it->GetAccessors();
1587  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1588  // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by the
1589  // global proxy.
1590  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1591  receiver =
1592  direct_handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), isolate);
1593  }
1594 
1595  // We should never get here to initialize a const with the hole value since a
1596  // const declaration would conflict with the setter.
1597  DCHECK(!IsForeign(*structure));
1598 
1599  // API style callbacks.
1600  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1601  if (IsAccessorInfo(*structure)) {
1602  DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
1603  auto info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(structure);
1604 
1605  if (!info->has_setter(isolate)) {
1606  // TODO(verwaest): We should not get here anymore once all AccessorInfos
1607  // are marked as special_data_property. They cannot both be writable and
1608  // not have a setter.
1609  return Just(true);
1610  }
1611 
1612  if (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1613  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1614  isolate, receiver, Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1615  Nothing<bool>());
1616  }
1617 
1618  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, info->data(), *receiver, *holder,
1619  maybe_should_throw);
1620  bool result = args.CallAccessorSetter(info, name, value);
1621  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
1622  // Ensure the setter callback respects the "should throw" value - it's
1623  // allowed to fail without throwing only in case of kDontThrow.
1624  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!result,
1625  GetShouldThrow(isolate, maybe_should_throw) == kDontThrow);
1626  return Just(result);
1627  }
1628 
1629  // Regular accessor.
1630  DirectHandle<Object> setter(Cast<AccessorPair>(*structure)->setter(),
1631  isolate);
1632  if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
1633  SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate, holder->GetCreationContext().value());
1634  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {value};
1635  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1636  isolate,
1637  Builtins::InvokeApiFunction(
1638  isolate, false, Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(setter), receiver,
1639  base::VectorOf(args), isolate->factory()->undefined_value()),
1640  Nothing<bool>());
1641  return Just(true);
1642  } else if (IsCallable(*setter)) {
1643  // TODO(rossberg): nicer would be to cast to some JSCallable here...
1644  return SetPropertyWithDefinedSetter(receiver, Cast<JSReceiver>(setter),
1645  value, maybe_should_throw);
1646  }
1647 
1648  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, maybe_should_throw),
1649  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoSetterInCallback,
1650  it->GetName(), it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
1651 }
1652 
1653 MaybeHandle<JSAny> Object::GetPropertyWithDefinedGetter(
1654  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> getter) {
1655  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
1656 
1657  // Platforms with simulators like arm/arm64 expose a funny issue. If the
1658  // simulator has a separate JS stack pointer from the C++ stack pointer, it
1659  // can miss C++ stack overflows in the stack guard at the start of JavaScript
1660  // functions. It would be very expensive to check the C++ stack pointer at
1661  // that location. The best solution seems to be to break the impasse by
1662  // adding checks at possible recursion points. What's more, we don't put
1663  // this stack check behind the USE_SIMULATOR define in order to keep
1664  // behavior the same between hardware and simulators.
1665  StackLimitCheck check(isolate);
1666  if (check.JsHasOverflowed()) {
1667  isolate->StackOverflow();
1668  return kNullMaybeHandle;
1669  }
1670 
1671  return Cast<JSAny>(Execution::Call(isolate, getter, receiver, {}));
1672 }
1673 
1674 Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyWithDefinedSetter(
1675  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> setter,
1676  DirectHandle<Object> value, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1677  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
1678 
1679  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {value};
1680  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1681  isolate, Execution::Call(isolate, setter, receiver, base::VectorOf(args)),
1682  Nothing<bool>());
1683  return Just(true);
1684 }

1686 // static
1687 Tagged<Map> Object::GetPrototypeChainRootMap(Tagged<Object> obj,
1688  Isolate* isolate) {
1689  DisallowGarbageCollection no_alloc;
1690  if (IsSmi(obj)) {
1691  Tagged<Context> native_context = isolate->context()->native_context();
1692  return native_context->number_function()->initial_map();
1693  }
1694 
1695  const Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(obj);
1696  return heap_object->map()->GetPrototypeChainRootMap(isolate);
1697 }

1699 // static
1700 Tagged<Smi> Object::GetOrCreateHash(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
1701  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1702  Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetSimpleHash(obj);
1703  if (IsSmi(hash)) return Cast<Smi>(hash);
1704 
1705  DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(obj));
1706  return Cast<JSReceiver>(obj)->GetOrCreateIdentityHash(isolate);
1707 }
1708 
1709 // static
1710 bool Object::SameValue(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> other) {
1711  if (other == obj) return true;
1712 
1713  if (IsNumber(obj) && IsNumber(other)) {
1714  return SameNumberValue(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(obj)),
1715  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(other)));
1716  }
1717  if (IsString(obj) && IsString(other)) {
1718  return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(other));
1719  }
1720  if (IsBigInt(obj) && IsBigInt(other)) {
1721  return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(other));
1722  }
1723  return false;
1724 }
1725 
1726 // static
1727 bool Object::SameValueZero(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> other) {
1728  if (other == obj) return true;
1729 
1730  if (IsNumber(obj) && IsNumber(other)) {
1731  double this_value = Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(obj));
1732  double other_value = Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(other));
1733  // +0 == -0 is true
1734  return this_value == other_value ||
1735  (std::isnan(this_value) && std::isnan(other_value));
1736  }
1737  if (IsString(obj) && IsString(other)) {
1738  return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(other));
1739  }
1740  if (IsBigInt(obj) && IsBigInt(other)) {
1741  return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(other));
1742  }
1743  return false;
1744 }
1745 
1746 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::ArraySpeciesConstructor(
1747  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSAny> original_array) {
1748  DirectHandle<Object> default_species = isolate->array_function();
1749  if (!v8_flags.builtin_subclassing) return default_species;
1750  if (IsJSArray(*original_array) &&
1751  Cast<JSArray>(original_array)->HasArrayPrototype(isolate) &&
1752  Protectors::IsArraySpeciesLookupChainIntact(isolate)) {
1753  return default_species;
1754  }
1755  DirectHandle<Object> constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1756  Maybe<bool> is_array = IsArray(original_array);
1757  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(is_array);
1758  if (is_array.FromJust()) {
1759  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1760  isolate, constructor,
1761  Object::GetProperty(isolate, original_array,
1762  isolate->factory()->constructor_string()));
1763  if (IsConstructor(*constructor)) {
1764  DirectHandle<NativeContext> constructor_context;
1765  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1766  isolate, constructor_context,
1767  JSReceiver::GetFunctionRealm(Cast<JSReceiver>(constructor)));
1768  if (*constructor_context != *isolate->native_context() &&
1769  *constructor == constructor_context->array_function()) {
1770  constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1771  }
1772  }
1773  if (IsJSReceiver(*constructor)) {
1774  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1775  isolate, constructor,
1776  JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(constructor),
1777  isolate->factory()->species_symbol()));
1778  if (IsNull(*constructor, isolate)) {
1779  constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1780  }
1781  }
1782  }
1783  if (IsUndefined(*constructor, isolate)) {
1784  return default_species;
1785  } else {
1786  if (!IsConstructor(*constructor)) {
1787  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1788  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSpeciesNotConstructor));
1789  }
1790  return constructor;
1791  }
1792 }
1793 
1794 // ES6 section 7.3.20 SpeciesConstructor ( O, defaultConstructor )
1795 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::SpeciesConstructor(
1796  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> recv,
1797  DirectHandle<JSFunction> default_ctor) {
1798  DirectHandle<Object> ctor_obj;
1799  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1800  isolate, ctor_obj,
1801  JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, recv,
1802  isolate->factory()->constructor_string()));
1803 
1804  if (IsUndefined(*ctor_obj, isolate)) return default_ctor;
1805 
1806  if (!IsJSReceiver(*ctor_obj)) {
1807  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1808  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kConstructorNotReceiver));
1809  }
1810 
1811  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> ctor = Cast<JSReceiver>(ctor_obj);
1812 
1813  DirectHandle<Object> species;
1814  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1815  isolate, species,
1816  JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, ctor,
1817  isolate->factory()->species_symbol()));
1818 
1819  if (IsNullOrUndefined(*species, isolate)) {
1820  return default_ctor;
1821  }
1822 
1823  if (IsConstructor(*species)) return species;
1824 
1825  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1826  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSpeciesNotConstructor));
1827 }
1828 
1829 // static
1830 bool Object::IterationHasObservableEffects(Tagged<Object> obj) {
1831  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1832  // Check that this object is an array.
1833  if (!IsJSArray(obj)) return true;
1834  Tagged<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(obj);
1835 
1836  // Check that we have the original ArrayPrototype.
1837  Tagged<Object> array_proto = array->map()->prototype();
1838  if (!IsJSObject(array_proto)) return true;
1839  Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = array->GetCreationContext().value();
1840  auto initial_array_prototype = native_context->initial_array_prototype();
1841  if (initial_array_prototype != array_proto) return true;
1842 
1843  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
1844  // Check that the ArrayPrototype hasn't been modified in a way that would
1845  // affect iteration.
1846  if (!Protectors::IsArrayIteratorLookupChainIntact(isolate)) return true;
1847 
1848  // For FastPacked kinds, iteration will have the same effect as simply
1849  // accessing each property in order.
1850  ElementsKind array_kind = array->GetElementsKind();
1851  if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(array_kind)) return false;
1852 
1853  // For FastHoley kinds, an element access on a hole would cause a lookup on
1854  // the prototype. This could have different results if the prototype has been
1855  // changed.
1856  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(array_kind) &&
1857  Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate)) {
1858  return false;
1859  }
1860  return true;
1861 }
1862 
1863 // static
1864 bool Object::IsCodeLike(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
1865  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1866  return IsJSReceiver(obj) && Cast<JSReceiver>(obj)->IsCodeLike(isolate);
1867 }

1912  }

1942 
1943 int HeapObject::SizeFromMap(Tagged<Map> map) const {
1944  int instance_size = map->instance_size();
1945  if (instance_size != kVariableSizeSentinel) return instance_size;
1946  // Only inline the most frequent cases.
1947  InstanceType instance_type = map->instance_type();
1948  if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
1949  LAST_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
1950  return UncheckedCast<FixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1951  }
1952 #define CASE(TypeCamelCase, TYPE_UPPER_CASE) \
1953  if (instance_type == TYPE_UPPER_CASE##_TYPE) { \
1954  return UncheckedCast<TypeCamelCase>(*this)->AllocatedSize(); \
1955  }
1956  SIMPLE_HEAP_OBJECT_LIST2(CASE)
1957 #undef CASE
1958  if (instance_type == SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS_TYPE) {
1959  return UncheckedCast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1960  }
1961  if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_CONTEXT_TYPE, LAST_CONTEXT_TYPE)) {
1962  if (instance_type == NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE) return NativeContext::kSize;
1963  return Context::SizeFor(UncheckedCast<Context>(*this)->length());
1964  }
1965  if (instance_type == SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1966  instance_type == INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1967  instance_type == SHARED_SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE) {
1968  // Strings may get concurrently truncated, hence we have to access its
1969  // length synchronized.
1970  return SeqOneByteString::SizeFor(
1971  UncheckedCast<SeqOneByteString>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1972  }
1973  if (instance_type == BYTECODE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1974  return BytecodeArray::SizeFor(
1975  UncheckedCast<BytecodeArray>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1976  }
1977  if (instance_type == FREE_SPACE_TYPE) {
1978  return UncheckedCast<FreeSpace>(*this)->size(kRelaxedLoad);
1979  }
1980  if (instance_type == SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1981  instance_type == INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1982  instance_type == SHARED_SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE) {
1983  // Strings may get concurrently truncated, hence we have to access its
1984  // length synchronized.
1985  return SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(
1986  UncheckedCast<SeqTwoByteString>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1987  }
1988  if (instance_type == FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1989  return UncheckedCast<FixedDoubleArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1990  }
1991  if (instance_type == TRUSTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1992  return UncheckedCast<TrustedFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1993  }
1994  if (instance_type == PROTECTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1995  return UncheckedCast<ProtectedFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1996  }
1997  if (instance_type == PROTECTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1998  return UncheckedCast<ProtectedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1999  }
2000  if (instance_type == TRUSTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2001  return UncheckedCast<TrustedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2002  }
2003  if (instance_type == TRUSTED_BYTE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2004  return UncheckedCast<TrustedByteArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2005  }
2006  if (instance_type == FEEDBACK_METADATA_TYPE) {
2007  return UncheckedCast<FeedbackMetadata>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2008  }
2009  if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE,
2010  LAST_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
2011  return DescriptorArray::SizeFor(
2012  UncheckedCast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_all_descriptors());
2013  }
2014  if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
2015  LAST_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
2016  return UncheckedCast<WeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2017  }
2018  if (instance_type == WEAK_ARRAY_LIST_TYPE) {
2019  return UncheckedCast<WeakArrayList>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2020  }
2021  if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE) {
2022  return SmallOrderedHashSet::SizeFor(
2023  UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedHashSet>(*this)->Capacity());
2024  }
2025  if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE) {
2026  return SmallOrderedHashMap::SizeFor(
2027  UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->Capacity());
2028  }
2029  if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE) {
2030  return SmallOrderedNameDictionary::SizeFor(
2031  UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->Capacity());
2032  }
2033  if (instance_type == SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE) {
2034  return SwissNameDictionary::SizeFor(
2035  UncheckedCast<SwissNameDictionary>(*this)->Capacity());
2036  }
2037  if (instance_type == PROPERTY_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2038  return PropertyArray::SizeFor(
2039  UncheckedCast<PropertyArray>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
2040  }
2041  if (instance_type == FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE) {
2042  return FeedbackVector::SizeFor(
2043  UncheckedCast<FeedbackVector>(*this)->length());
2044  }
2045  if (instance_type == BIGINT_TYPE) {
2046  return BigInt::SizeFor(UncheckedCast<BigInt>(*this)->length());
2047  }
2048  if (instance_type == PREPARSE_DATA_TYPE) {
2049  Tagged<PreparseData> data = UncheckedCast<PreparseData>(*this);
2050  return PreparseData::SizeFor(data->data_length(), data->children_length());
2051  }
2052 #define MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR(TYPE, TypeName) \
2053  if (instance_type == TYPE) { \
2054  return UncheckedCast<TypeName>(*this)->AllocatedSize(); \
2055  }
2056  TORQUE_INSTANCE_TYPE_TO_BODY_DESCRIPTOR_LIST(MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR)
2057 #undef MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR
2058 
2059  if (instance_type == INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE) {
2060  return UncheckedCast<InstructionStream>(*this)->Size();
2061  }
2062  if (instance_type == COVERAGE_INFO_TYPE) {
2063  return CoverageInfo::SizeFor(
2064  UncheckedCast<CoverageInfo>(*this)->slot_count());
2065  }
2066 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2067  if (instance_type == WASM_TYPE_INFO_TYPE) {
2068  return WasmTypeInfo::SizeFor(
2069  UncheckedCast<WasmTypeInfo>(*this)->supertypes_length());
2070  }
2071  if (instance_type == WASM_STRUCT_TYPE) {
2072  return WasmStruct::GcSafeSize(map);
2073  }
2074  if (instance_type == WASM_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2075  return WasmArray::SizeFor(map, UncheckedCast<WasmArray>(*this)->length());
2076  }
2077  if (instance_type == WASM_NULL_TYPE) {
2078  return WasmNull::kSize;
2079  }
2080  if (instance_type == WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE) {
2081  return WasmDispatchTable::SizeFor(
2082  UncheckedCast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->capacity());
2083  }
2084 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2085  if (instance_type == DOUBLE_STRING_CACHE_TYPE) {
2086  return DoubleStringCache::SizeFor(
2087  UncheckedCast<DoubleStringCache>(*this)->capacity());
2088  }
2089  if (instance_type == EMBEDDER_DATA_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2090  return EmbedderDataArray::SizeFor(
2091  UncheckedCast<EmbedderDataArray>(*this)->length());
2092  }
2093  UNREACHABLE();
2094 }
