2096 bool HeapObject::NeedsRehashing(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) const {
2097  return NeedsRehashing(map(cage_base)->instance_type());
2098 }
2099 
2100 bool HeapObject::NeedsRehashing(InstanceType instance_type) const {
2101  if (V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL) {
2102  // Use map() only when it's guaranteed that it's not an InstructionStream
2103  // object.
2104  DCHECK_IMPLIES(instance_type != INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE,
2105  instance_type == map()->instance_type());
2106  } else {
2107  DCHECK_EQ(instance_type, map()->instance_type());
2108  }
2109  switch (instance_type) {
2110  case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2111  case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2112  return Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_descriptors() > 1;
2113  case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2114  return Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->number_of_transitions() > 1;
2115  case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2116  case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2117  return false; // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2118  case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2119  case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2120  case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2121  case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2122  case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2123  case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2124  case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2125  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2126  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2127  case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2128  case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2129  case JS_MAP_TYPE:
2130  case JS_SET_TYPE:
2131  return true;
2132  default:
2133  return false;
2134  }
2135  UNREACHABLE();
2136 }
2137 
2138 bool HeapObject::CanBeRehashed(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) const {
2139  DCHECK(NeedsRehashing(cage_base));
2140  switch (map(cage_base)->instance_type()) {
2141  case JS_MAP_TYPE:
2142  case JS_SET_TYPE:
2143  return true;
2144  case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2145  case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2146  UNREACHABLE(); // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2147  case ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2148  return false;
2149  case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2150  case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2151  case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2152  case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2153  case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2154  case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2155  case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2156  return true;
2157  case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2158  case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2159  return true;
2160  case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2161  return true;
2162  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2163  return Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2164  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2165  return Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2166  case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2167  return Cast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2168  default:
2169  return false;
2170  }
2171  UNREACHABLE();
2172 }
2173 
2174 template <typename IsolateT>
2175 void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(IsolateT* isolate) {
2176  switch (map(isolate)->instance_type()) {
2177  case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2178  Cast<ObjectHashTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2179  break;
2180  case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2181  Cast<NameDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2182  break;
2183  case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2184  Cast<NameToIndexHashTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2185  break;
2186  case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2187  Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2188  break;
2189  case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2190  Cast<SwissNameDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2191  break;
2192  case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2193  Cast<GlobalDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2194  break;
2195  case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2196  Cast<NumberDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2197  break;
2198  case SIMPLE_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2199  Cast<SimpleNameDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2200  break;
2201  case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2202  Cast<SimpleNumberDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2203  break;
2204  case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2205  case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2206  DCHECK_LE(1, Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_descriptors());
2207  Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->Sort();
2208  break;
2209  case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2210  Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->Sort();
2211  break;
2212  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2213  DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2214  break;
2215  case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2216  DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedHashSet>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2217  break;
2218  case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2219  case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2220  UNREACHABLE(); // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2221  case JS_MAP_TYPE: {
2222  Cast<JSMap>(*this)->Rehash(isolate->AsIsolate());
2223  break;
2224  }
2225  case JS_SET_TYPE: {
2226  Cast<JSSet>(*this)->Rehash(isolate->AsIsolate());
2227  break;
2228  }
2229  case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2230  DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2231  break;
2232  case INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2233  case INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2234  // Rare case, rehash read-only space strings before they are sealed.
2235  DCHECK(ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(*this));
2236  Cast<String>(*this)->EnsureHash();
2237  break;
2238  default:
2239  // TODO(ishell): remove once b/326043780 is no longer an issue.
2240  isolate->AsIsolate()->PushParamsAndDie(
2241  reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptr()), reinterpret_cast<void*>(map().ptr()),
2242  reinterpret_cast<void*>(
2243  static_cast<uintptr_t>(map()->instance_type())));
2244  UNREACHABLE();
2245  }
2246 }
2247 template void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(Isolate* isolate);
2248 template void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(LocalIsolate* isolate);
2249 
2250 void DescriptorArray::GeneralizeAllFields(bool clear_constness) {
2251  int length = number_of_descriptors();
2252  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(length)) {
2253  PropertyDetails details = GetDetails(i);
2254  details = details.CopyWithRepresentation(Representation::Tagged());
2255  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
2256  // Since constness is not propagated across proto transitions we must
2257  // clear the flag here.
2258  if (clear_constness) {
2259  details = details.CopyWithConstness(PropertyConstness::kMutable);
2260  }
2261  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
2262  SetValue(i, FieldType::Any());
2263  }
2264  SetDetails(i, details);
2265  }
2266 }
2267 
2268 MaybeHandle<Object> Object::SetProperty(Isolate* isolate,
2269  DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
2270  DirectHandle<Name> name,
2271  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2272  StoreOrigin store_origin,
2273  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2274  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, name);
2275  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(SetProperty(&it, value, store_origin, should_throw));
2276  return indirect_handle(value, isolate);
2277 }
2278 
2279 Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyInternal(LookupIterator* it,
2280  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2281  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2282  StoreOrigin store_origin, bool* found) {
2283  it->UpdateProtector();
2284  DCHECK(it->IsFound());
2285 
2286  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
2287  // interceptor calls.
2288  AssertNoContextChange ncc(it->isolate());
2289 
2290  for (;; it->Next()) {
2291  switch (it->state()) {
2292  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2293  if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
2294  // Check whether it makes sense to reuse the lookup iterator. Here it
2295  // might still call into setters up the prototype chain.
2296  return JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(it, value,
2297  should_throw);
2298 
2299  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2300  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
2301  // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by
2302  // the global proxy.
2303  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
2304  receiver = direct_handle(
2305  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), it->isolate());
2306  }
2307  return JSProxy::SetProperty(it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), it->GetName(),
2308  value, receiver, should_throw);
2309  }
2310 
2311  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2312  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
2313 
2314  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
2315  if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2316  InterceptorResult result;
2317  if (!JSObject::SetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw, value)
2318  .To(&result)) {
2319  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
2320  return Nothing<bool>();
2321  }
2322  switch (result) {
2323  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
2324  return Just(false);
2325  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
2326  return Just(true);
2327  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
2328  // Proceed lookup.
2329  break;
2330  }
2331  // Assuming that the callback has side effects, we use
2332  // Object::SetSuperProperty() which works properly regardless on
2333  // whether the property was present on the receiver or not when
2334  // storing to the receiver.
2335  // Proceed lookup from the next state.
2336  it->Next();
2337  } else {
2338  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe_attributes =
2339  JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
2340  if (maybe_attributes.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
2341  if ((maybe_attributes.FromJust() & READ_ONLY) != 0) {
2342  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2343  }
2344  // At this point we might have called interceptor's query or getter
2345  // callback. Assuming that the callbacks have side effects, we use
2346  // Object::SetSuperProperty() which works properly regardless on
2347  // whether the property was present on the receiver or not when
2348  // storing to the receiver.
2349  if (maybe_attributes.FromJust() == ABSENT) {
2350  // Proceed lookup from the next state.
2351  it->Next();
2352  } else {
2353  // Finish lookup in order to make Object::SetSuperProperty() store
2354  // property to the receiver.
2355  it->NotFound();
2356  }
2357  }
2358  return Object::SetSuperProperty(it, value, store_origin, should_throw);
2359  }
2360 
2361  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
2362  if (it->IsReadOnly()) {
2363  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2364  }
2365  DirectHandle<Object> accessors = it->GetAccessors();
2366  if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors) &&
2367  !it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2368  *found = false;
2369  return Nothing<bool>();
2370  }
2371  return SetPropertyWithAccessor(it, value, should_throw);
2372  }
2373  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND: {
2374  // IntegerIndexedElementSet converts value to a Number/BigInt prior to
2375  // the bounds check. The bounds check has already happened here, but
2376  // perform the possibly effectful ToNumber (or ToBigInt) operation
2377  // anyways.
2378  DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> holder = it->GetHolder<JSTypedArray>();
2379 
2380  // The index found case uses HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()
2381  // in below "case LookupIterator::DATA" to check
2382  // "i. If SameValue(O, Receiver) is true..." of the spec.
2383  // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-typedarray-set
2384  if (it->HolderIsReceiver()) {
2385  DirectHandle<Object> converted_value;
2386 
2387  if (holder->type() == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
2388  holder->type() == kExternalBigUint64Array) {
2389  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2390  it->isolate(), converted_value,
2391  BigInt::FromObject(it->isolate(), value), Nothing<bool>());
2392  } else {
2393  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2394  it->isolate(), converted_value,
2395  Object::ToNumber(it->isolate(), value), Nothing<bool>());
2396  }
2397  // For RAB/GSABs, the above conversion might grow the buffer so that
2398  // the index is no longer out of bounds. Redo the bounds check and try
2399  // again.
2400  it->RecheckTypedArrayBounds();
2401  value = converted_value;
2402  }
2403  if (it->state() != LookupIterator::DATA) {
2404  // Still out of bounds.
2405  DCHECK_EQ(it->state(), LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND);
2406 
2407  // FIXME: Throw a TypeError if the holder is detached here
2408  // (IntegerIndexedElementSet step 5).
2409 
2410  // TODO(verwaest): Per spec, we should return false here (steps 6-9
2411  // in IntegerIndexedElementSet), resulting in an exception being
2412  // thrown on OOB accesses in strict code. Historically, v8 has not
2413  // done made this change due to uncertainty about web compat.
2414  // (v8:4901)
2415  return Just(true);
2416  }
2417  [[fallthrough]];
2418  }
2419 
2420  case LookupIterator::DATA:
2421  if (it->IsReadOnly()) {
2422  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2423  }
2424  if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2425  return SetDataProperty(it, value);
2426  }
2427  [[fallthrough]];
2428  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2429  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
2430  *found = false;
2431  return Nothing<bool>();
2432 
2433  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
2434  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2435  }
2436  UNREACHABLE();
2437  }
2438 }
2439 
2440 bool Object::CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(
2441  LookupIterator* it, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2442  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2443 
2444  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*it->GetReceiver(), isolate) &&
2445  (GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw) == ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)) {
2446  if (it->state() == LookupIterator::TRANSITION) {
2447  // The property cell that we have created is garbage because we are going
2448  // to throw now instead of putting it into the global dictionary. However,
2449  // the cell might already have been stored into the feedback vector, so
2450  // we must invalidate it nevertheless.
2451  it->transition_cell()->ClearAndInvalidate(isolate);
2452  }
2453  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewReferenceError(
2454  MessageTemplate::kNotDefined, it->GetName()));
2455  return false;
2456  }
2457  return true;
2458 }
2459 
2460 Maybe<bool> Object::SetProperty(LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2461  StoreOrigin store_origin,
2462  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2463  if (it->IsFound()) {
2464  bool found = true;
2465  Maybe<bool> result =
2466  SetPropertyInternal(it, value, should_throw, store_origin, &found);
2467  if (found) return result;
2468  }
2469 
2470  if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(it, should_throw)) {
2471  return Nothing<bool>();
2472  }
2473  return AddDataProperty(it, value, NONE, should_throw, store_origin);
2474 }
2475 
2476 Maybe<bool> Object::SetSuperProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2477  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2478  StoreOrigin store_origin,
2479  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2480  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2481 
2482  if (it->IsFound()) {
2483  bool found = true;
2484  Maybe<bool> result =
2485  SetPropertyInternal(it, value, should_throw, store_origin, &found);
2486  if (found) return result;
2487  }
2488 
2489  it->UpdateProtector();
2490 
2491  // The property either doesn't exist on the holder or exists there as a data
2492  // property.
2493 
2494  if (!IsJSReceiver(*it->GetReceiver())) {
2495  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2496  }
2497  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
2498 
2499  // Note, the callers rely on the fact that this code is redoing the full own
2500  // lookup from scratch.
2501  LookupIterator own_lookup(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
2502  LookupIterator::OWN);
2503  for (;; own_lookup.Next()) {
2504  switch (own_lookup.state()) {
2505  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2506  if (!own_lookup.HasAccess()) {
2507  return JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(&own_lookup, value,
2508  should_throw);
2509  }
2510  continue;
2511 
2512  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
2513  if (IsAccessorInfo(*own_lookup.GetAccessors())) {
2514  if (own_lookup.IsReadOnly()) {
2515  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(&own_lookup, value, should_throw);
2516  }
2517  return Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(&own_lookup, value,
2518  should_throw);
2519  }
2520  [[fallthrough]];
2521  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
2522  return RedefineIncompatibleProperty(isolate, it->GetName(), value,
2523  should_throw);
2524 
2525  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
2526  UNREACHABLE();
2527 
2528  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
2529  if (own_lookup.IsReadOnly()) {
2530  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(&own_lookup, value, should_throw);
2531  }
2532  return SetDataProperty(&own_lookup, value);
2533  }
2534 
2535  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
2536  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2537  PropertyDescriptor desc;
2538  Maybe<bool> owned =
2539  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&own_lookup, &desc);
2540  MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2541  if (!owned.FromJust()) {
2542  // |own_lookup| might become outdated at this point anyway.
2543  // TODO(leszeks): Remove this restart since we don't really use the
2544  // lookup iterator after this.
2545  own_lookup.Restart();
2546  if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(&own_lookup,
2547  should_throw)) {
2548  return Nothing<bool>();
2549  }
2550  return JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
2551  value, should_throw);
2552  }
2553  if (PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&desc) ||
2554  !desc.writable()) {
2555  return RedefineIncompatibleProperty(isolate, it->GetName(), value,
2556  should_throw);
2557  }
2558 
2559  PropertyDescriptor value_desc;
2560  value_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
2561  return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, it->GetName(),
2562  &value_desc, should_throw);
2563  }
2564 
2565  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2566  if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(&own_lookup, should_throw)) {
2567  return Nothing<bool>();
2568  }
2569  return AddDataProperty(&own_lookup, value, NONE, should_throw,
2570  store_origin);
2571 
2572  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2573  RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
2574  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2575 
2576  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
2577  UNREACHABLE();
2578  }
2579  UNREACHABLE();
2580  }
2581 }

2583 Maybe<bool> Object::CannotCreateProperty(Isolate* isolate,
2584  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
2585  DirectHandle<Object> name,
2586  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2587  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2588  RETURN_FAILURE(
2589  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
2590  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictCannotCreateProperty, name,
2591  Object::TypeOf(isolate, receiver), receiver));
2592 }

2594 Maybe<bool> Object::WriteToReadOnlyProperty(
2595  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2596  Maybe<ShouldThrow> maybe_should_throw) {
2597  ShouldThrow should_throw = GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), maybe_should_throw);
2598  if (it->IsFound() &&
2599  it->state() != LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT &&
2600  !it->HolderIsReceiver()) {
2601  // "Override mistake" attempted, record a use count to track this per
2602  // v8:8175
2603  v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature feature =
2604  should_throw == kThrowOnError
2605  ? v8::Isolate::kAttemptOverrideReadOnlyOnPrototypeStrict
2606  : v8::Isolate::kAttemptOverrideReadOnlyOnPrototypeSloppy;
2607  it->isolate()->CountUsage(feature);
2608  }
2609  return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetReceiver(),
2610  it->GetName(), value, should_throw);
2611 }

2630 Maybe<bool> Object::SetDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2631  DirectHandle<Object> value) {
2632  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2633  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver(), isolate),
2634  it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
2635  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!it->IsElement() && it->GetName()->IsPrivateName(),
2636  it->state() == LookupIterator::DATA);
2637  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
2638 
2639  // Store on the holder which may be hidden behind the receiver.
2640  DCHECK(it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype());
2641 
2642  DirectHandle<Object> to_assign = value;
2643  // Convert the incoming value to a number for storing into typed arrays.
2644  if (it->IsElement() && IsJSObject(*receiver, isolate) &&
2645  Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements(
2646  isolate)) {
2647  auto receiver_ta = Cast<JSTypedArray>(receiver);
2648  ElementsKind elements_kind = Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->GetElementsKind();
2649  if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
2650  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, to_assign,
2651  BigInt::FromObject(isolate, value),
2652  Nothing<bool>());
2653  if (V8_UNLIKELY(receiver_ta->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
2654  it->index() >= receiver_ta->GetLength())) {
2655  return Just(true);
2656  }
2657  } else if (!IsNumber(*value) && !IsUndefined(*value, isolate)) {
2658  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, to_assign,
2659  Object::ToNumber(isolate, value),
2660  Nothing<bool>());
2661  if (V8_UNLIKELY(receiver_ta->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
2662  it->index() >= receiver_ta->GetLength())) {
2663  return Just(true);
2664  }
2665  }
2666  }
2667 
2668  DCHECK(!IsWasmObject(*receiver, isolate));
2669  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsJSSharedStruct(*receiver, isolate) ||
2670  IsJSSharedArray(*receiver, isolate))) {
2671  // Shared structs can only point to primitives or shared values.
2672  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2673  isolate, to_assign, Object::Share(isolate, to_assign, kThrowOnError),
2674  Nothing<bool>());
2675  it->WriteDataValue(to_assign, false);
2676  } else {
2677  // Possibly migrate to the most up-to-date map that will be able to store
2678  // |value| under it->name().
2679  it->PrepareForDataProperty(to_assign);
2680 
2681  // Write the property value.
2682  it->WriteDataValue(to_assign, false);
2683  }
2684 
2685 #if VERIFY_HEAP
2686  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
2687  receiver->HeapObjectVerify(isolate);
2688  }
2689 #endif
2690  return Just(true);
2691 }
2692 
2693 Maybe<bool> Object::AddDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2694  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2695  PropertyAttributes attributes,
2696  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2697  StoreOrigin store_origin,
2698  EnforceDefineSemantics semantics) {
2699  if (!IsJSReceiver(*it->GetReceiver())) {
2700  return CannotCreateProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetReceiver(), it->GetName(),
2701  value, should_throw);
2702  }
2703 
2704  // Private symbols should be installed on JSProxy using
2705  // JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol.
2706  if (IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver()) && it->GetName()->IsPrivate() &&
2707  !it->GetName()->IsPrivateName()) {
2708  RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), should_throw),
2709  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyPrivate));
2710  }
2711 
2712  DCHECK_NE(LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND, it->state());
2713 
2714  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>();
2715  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*receiver), it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
2716  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*receiver),
2717  it->state() == LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND);
2718 
2719  // If the receiver is a JSGlobalProxy, store on the prototype (JSGlobalObject)
2720  // instead. If the prototype is Null, the proxy is detached.
2721  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) return Just(true);
2722 
2723  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2724 
2725  if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) {
2726  if (IsWasmObject(*receiver)) {
2727  RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
2728  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2729  }
2730  bool is_shared_object = IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*receiver);
2731  RETURN_FAILURE(
2732  isolate, GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), should_throw),
2733  NewTypeError(
2734  semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine
2735  ? (is_shared_object
2736  ? MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowedFixedLayout
2737  : MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed)
2738  : (is_shared_object ? MessageTemplate::kObjectFixedLayout
2739  : MessageTemplate::kObjectNotExtensible),
2740  it->GetName()));
2741  }
2742 
2743  if (it->IsElement(*receiver)) {
2744  if (IsJSArray(*receiver)) {
2745  DirectHandle<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(receiver);
2746  if (JSArray::WouldChangeReadOnlyLength(array, it->array_index())) {
2747  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
2748  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictReadOnlyProperty,
2749  isolate->factory()->length_string(),
2750  Object::TypeOf(isolate, array), array));
2751  }
2752  }
2753 
2754  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver_obj = Cast<JSObject>(receiver);
2755  MAYBE_RETURN(JSObject::AddDataElement(isolate, receiver_obj,
2756  it->array_index(), value, attributes),
2757  Nothing<bool>());
2758  JSObject::ValidateElements(isolate, *receiver_obj);
2759  return Just(true);
2760  }
2761 
2762  return Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(it, value, attributes,
2763  should_throw, store_origin);
2764 }
2765 
2766 // static
2767 Maybe<bool> Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(
2768  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2769  PropertyAttributes attributes, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2770  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
2771  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>();
2772  it->UpdateProtector();
2773  // Migrate to the most up-to-date map that will be able to store |value|
2774  // under it->name() with |attributes|.
2775  it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, attributes,
2776  store_origin);
2777  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::TRANSITION, it->state());
2778  it->ApplyTransitionToDataProperty(receiver);
2779 
2780  // Write the property value.
2781  it->WriteDataValue(value, true);
2782 
2783 #if VERIFY_HEAP
2784  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
2785  receiver->HeapObjectVerify(it->isolate());
2786  }
2787 #endif
2788 
2789  return Just(true);
2790 }

2792 // static
2793 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
2794  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
2795 typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType Object::ShareSlow(
2796  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<HeapObject> value,
2797  ShouldThrow throw_if_cannot_be_shared) {
2798  // Use Object::Share() if value might already be shared.
2799  DCHECK(!IsShared(*value));
2800 
2801  SharedObjectSafePublishGuard publish_guard;
2802 
2803  if (IsString(*value)) {
2804  return String::Share(isolate, Cast<String>(value));
2805  }
2806 
2807  if (IsHeapNumber(*value)) {
2808  uint64_t bits = Cast<HeapNumber>(*value)->value_as_bits();
2809  return isolate->factory()
2810  ->NewHeapNumberFromBits<AllocationType::kSharedOld>(bits);
2811  }
2812 
2813  if (throw_if_cannot_be_shared == kThrowOnError) {
2814  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2815  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotBeShared, value));
2816  }
2817  return {};
2818 }

2822  ShouldThrow throw_if_cannot_be_shared);

2827 namespace {
2828 
2829 template <class T>
2830 int AppendUniqueCallbacks(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<ArrayList> callbacks,
2831  DirectHandle<typename T::Array> array,
2832  int valid_descriptors) {
2833  int nof_callbacks = callbacks->length();
2834 
2835  // Fill in new callback descriptors. Process the callbacks from
2836  // back to front so that the last callback with a given name takes
2837  // precedence over previously added callbacks with that name.
2838  for (int i = nof_callbacks - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2839  DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry(Cast<AccessorInfo>(callbacks->get(i)),
2840  isolate);
2841  DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(entry->name()), isolate);
2842  DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*key));
2843  // Check if a descriptor with this name already exists before writing.
2844  if (!T::Contains(key, entry, valid_descriptors, array)) {
2845  T::Insert(key, entry, valid_descriptors, array);
2846  valid_descriptors++;
2847  }
2848  }
2849 
2850  return valid_descriptors;
2851 }
2852 
2853 struct FixedArrayAppender {
2854  using Array = FixedArray;
2855  static bool Contains(DirectHandle<Name> key, DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry,
2856  int valid_descriptors, DirectHandle<FixedArray> array) {
2857  for (int i = 0; i < valid_descriptors; i++) {
2858  if (*key == Cast<AccessorInfo>(array->get(i))->name()) return true;
2859  }
2860  return false;
2861  }
2862  static void Insert(DirectHandle<Name> key, DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry,
2863  int valid_descriptors, DirectHandle<FixedArray> array) {
2864  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2865  array->set(valid_descriptors, *entry);
2866  }
2867 };
2868 
2869 } // namespace
2870 
2871 int AccessorInfo::AppendUnique(Isolate* isolate,
2872  DirectHandle<Object> descriptors,
2873  DirectHandle<FixedArray> array,
2874  int valid_descriptors) {
2875  auto callbacks = Cast<ArrayList>(descriptors);
2876  DCHECK_GE(array->length(), callbacks->length() + valid_descriptors);
2877  return AppendUniqueCallbacks<FixedArrayAppender>(isolate, callbacks, array,
2878  valid_descriptors);
2879 }

2881 void JSProxy::Revoke(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
2882  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2883  // If this fails then some Proxy allocation code path that created
2884  // revocable Proxies didn't set the bit correctly.
2885  CHECK(JSProxy::IsRevocableBit::decode(proxy->flags()));
2886  // ES#sec-proxy-revocation-functions
2887  if (!proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2888  // 5. Set p.[[ProxyTarget]] to null.
2889  proxy->set_target(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).null_value());
2890  // 6. Set p.[[ProxyHandler]] to null.
2891  proxy->set_handler(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).null_value());
2892  }
2893  DCHECK(proxy->IsRevoked());
2894 }

2896 // static
2897 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::IsArray(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
2898  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2899  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object = Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy);
2900  for (int i = 0; i < JSProxy::kMaxIterationLimit; i++) {
2901  proxy = Cast<JSProxy>(object);
2902  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2903  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2904  MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked,
2905  isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked("IsArray")));
2906  return Nothing<bool>();
2907  }
2908  object = direct_handle(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
2909  if (IsJSArray(*object)) return Just(true);
2910  if (!IsJSProxy(*object)) return Just(false);
2911  }
2912 
2913  // Too deep recursion, throw a RangeError.
2914  isolate->StackOverflow();
2915  return Nothing<bool>();
2916 }

2918 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::HasProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
2919  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
2920  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
2921  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
2922  // 1. (Assert)
2923  // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
2924  DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
2925  // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
2926  // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
2927  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2928  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2929  MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, isolate->factory()->has_string()));
2930  return Nothing<bool>();
2931  }
2932  // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
2933  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
2934  // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "has").
2935  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
2936  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2937  isolate, trap,
2938  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler),
2939  isolate->factory()->has_string()),
2940  Nothing<bool>());
2941  // 7. If trap is undefined, then
2942  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
2943  // 7a. Return target.[[HasProperty]](P).
2944  return JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, target, name);
2945  }
2946  // 8. Let booleanTrapResult be ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, target, P)).
2947  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result_obj;
2948  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
2949  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2950  isolate, trap_result_obj,
2951  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
2952  Nothing<bool>());
2953  bool boolean_trap_result = Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result_obj, isolate);
2954  // 9. If booleanTrapResult is false, then:
2955  if (!boolean_trap_result) {
2956  MAYBE_RETURN(JSProxy::CheckHasTrap(isolate, name, target), Nothing<bool>());
2957  }
2958  // 10. Return booleanTrapResult.
2959  return Just(boolean_trap_result);
2960 }

2962 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::CheckHasTrap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name,
2963  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target) {
2964  // 9a. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
2965  PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
2966  Maybe<bool> target_found =
2967  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
2968  MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
2969  // 9b. If targetDesc is not undefined, then:
2970  if (target_found.FromJust()) {
2971  // 9b i. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError
2972  // exception.
2973  if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
2974  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2975  MessageTemplate::kProxyHasNonConfigurable, name));
2976  return Nothing<bool>();
2977  }
2978  // 9b ii. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
2979  Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
2980  MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
2981  // 9b iii. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
2982  if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
2983  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2984  MessageTemplate::kProxyHasNonExtensible, name));
2985  return Nothing<bool>();
2986  }
2987  }
2988  return Just(true);
2989 }

2991 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetProperty(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
2992  DirectHandle<Name> name,
2993  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2994  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
2995  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2996  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
2997  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2998  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
2999  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3000  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->set_string();
3001 
3002  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3003  isolate->Throw(
3004  *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3005  return Nothing<bool>();
3006  }
3007  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3008  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3009 
3010  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3011  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3012  isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3013  Nothing<bool>());
3014  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3015  PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
3016  LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, key, target);
3017 
3018  return Object::SetSuperProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
3019  should_throw);
3020  }
3021 
3022  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3023  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name, value, receiver};
3024  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3025  isolate, trap_result,
3026  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3027  Nothing<bool>());
3028  if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3029  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3030  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
3031  trap_name, name));
3032  }
3033 
3034  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
3035  JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(isolate, name, target, value, kSet);
3036 
3037  if (result.is_null()) {
3038  return Nothing<bool>();
3039  }
3040  return Just(true);
3041 }

3043 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::DeletePropertyOrElement(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3044  DirectHandle<Name> name,
3045  LanguageMode language_mode) {
3046  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
3047  ShouldThrow should_throw =
3048  is_sloppy(language_mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
3049  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
3050  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3051  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3052  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->deleteProperty_string();
3053 
3054  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3055  isolate->Throw(
3056  *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3057  return Nothing<bool>();
3058  }
3059  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3060  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3061 
3062  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3063  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3064  isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3065  Nothing<bool>());
3066  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3067  return JSReceiver::DeletePropertyOrElement(isolate, target, name,
3068  language_mode);
3069  }
3070 
3071  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3072  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
3073  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3074  isolate, trap_result,
3075  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3076  Nothing<bool>());
3077  if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3078  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
3079  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
3080  trap_name, name));
3081  }
3082 
3083  // Enforce the invariant.
3084  return JSProxy::CheckDeleteTrap(isolate, name, target);
3085 }

3087 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::CheckDeleteTrap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name,
3088  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target) {
3089  // 10. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3090  PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3091  Maybe<bool> target_found =
3092  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
3093  MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
3094  // 11. If targetDesc is undefined, return true.
3095  if (target_found.FromJust()) {
3096  // 12. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3097  if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
3098  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3099  MessageTemplate::kProxyDeletePropertyNonConfigurable, name));
3100  return Nothing<bool>();
3101  }
3102  // 13. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3103  Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3104  MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3105  // 14. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3106  if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
3107  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3108  MessageTemplate::kProxyDeletePropertyNonExtensible, name));
3109  return Nothing<bool>();
3110  }
3111  }
3112  return Just(true);
3113 }

3119  bool revocable) {

3122  }

3124  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyNonObject));
3125  }
3126  return isolate->factory()->NewJSProxy(Cast<JSReceiver>(target),
3127  Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), revocable);

3139 // TODO(jkummerow): Consider unification with FastAsArrayLength() in

3141 bool PropertyKeyToArrayLength(DirectHandle<Object> value, uint32_t* length) {
3142  DCHECK(IsNumber(*value) || IsName(*value));

3152 // ES6 9.4.2.1
3153 // static
3154 Maybe<bool> JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
3155  DirectHandle<JSArray> o,
3156  DirectHandle<Object> name,
3157  PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3158  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3159  if (IsName(*name)) {
3160  name = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(Cast<Name>(name));
3161  }
3162 
3163  // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true. ("P" is |name|.)
3164  // 2. If P is "length", then:
3165  if (*name == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).length_string()) {
3166  // 2a. Return ArraySetLength(A, Desc).
3167  return ArraySetLength(isolate, o, desc, should_throw);
3168  }
3169  // 3. Else if P is an array index, then:
3170  uint32_t index = 0;
3171  if (PropertyKeyToArrayIndex(name, &index)) {
3172  // 3a. Let oldLenDesc be OrdinaryGetOwnProperty(A, "length").
3173  PropertyDescriptor old_len_desc;
3174  Maybe<bool> success = GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
3175  isolate, o, isolate->factory()->length_string(), &old_len_desc);
3176  // 3b. (Assert)
3177  DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3178  USE(success);
3179  // 3c. Let oldLen be oldLenDesc.[[Value]].
3180  uint32_t old_len = 0;
3181  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*old_len_desc.value(), &old_len));
3182  // 3d. Let index be ToUint32(P).
3183  // (Already done above.)
3184  // 3e. (Assert)
3185  // 3f. If index >= oldLen and oldLenDesc.[[Writable]] is false,
3186  // return false.
3187  if (index >= old_len && old_len_desc.has_writable() &&
3188  !old_len_desc.writable()) {
3189  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3190  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, name));
3191  }
3192  // 3g. Let succeeded be OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, P, Desc).
3193  Maybe<bool> succeeded =
3194  OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o, name, desc, should_throw);
3195  // 3h. Assert: succeeded is not an abrupt completion.
3196  // In our case, if should_throw == kThrowOnError, it can be!
3197  // 3i. If succeeded is false, return false.
3198  if (succeeded.IsNothing() || !succeeded.FromJust()) return succeeded;
3199  // 3j. If index >= oldLen, then:
3200  if (index >= old_len) {
3201  // 3j i. Set oldLenDesc.[[Value]] to index + 1.
3202  old_len_desc.set_value(isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(index + 1));
3203  // 3j ii. Let succeeded be
3204  // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", oldLenDesc).
3205  succeeded = OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o,
3206  isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3207  &old_len_desc, should_throw);
3208  // 3j iii. Assert: succeeded is true.
3209  DCHECK(succeeded.FromJust());
3210  USE(succeeded);
3211  }
3212  // 3k. Return true.
3213  return Just(true);
3214  }
3215 
3216  // 4. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, P, Desc).
3217  return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o, name, desc, should_throw);
3218 }
3219 
3220 // Part of ES6 9.4.2.4 ArraySetLength.
3221 // static
3222 bool JSArray::AnythingToArrayLength(Isolate* isolate,
3223  DirectHandle<Object> length_object,
3224  uint32_t* output) {
3225  // Fast path: check numbers and strings that can be converted directly
3226  // and unobservably.
3227  if (Object::ToArrayLength(*length_object, output)) return true;
3228  if (IsString(*length_object) &&
3229  Cast<String>(length_object)->AsArrayIndex(output)) {
3230  return true;
3231  }
3232  // Slow path: follow steps in ES6 9.4.2.4 "ArraySetLength".
3233  // 3. Let newLen be ToUint32(Desc.[[Value]]).
3234  DirectHandle<Number> uint32_v;
3235  if (!Object::ToUint32(isolate, length_object).ToHandle(&uint32_v)) {
3236  // 4. ReturnIfAbrupt(newLen).
3237  return false;
3238  }
3239  // 5. Let numberLen be ToNumber(Desc.[[Value]]).
3240  DirectHandle<Number> number_v;
3241  if (!Object::ToNumber(isolate, length_object).ToHandle(&number_v)) {
3242  // 6. ReturnIfAbrupt(newLen).
3243  return false;
3244  }
3245  // 7. If newLen != numberLen, throw a RangeError exception.
3246  if (Object::NumberValue(*uint32_v) != Object::NumberValue(*number_v)) {
3247  DirectHandle<Object> exception =
3248  isolate->factory()->NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength);
3249  isolate->Throw(*exception);
3250  return false;
3251  }
3252  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*uint32_v, output));
3253  return true;
3254 }
3255 
3256 // ES6 9.4.2.4
3257 // static
3258 Maybe<bool> JSArray::ArraySetLength(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> a,
3259  PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3260  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3261  // 1. If the [[Value]] field of Desc is absent, then
3262  if (!desc->has_value()) {
3263  // 1a. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", Desc).
3264  return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
3265  isolate, a, isolate->factory()->length_string(), desc, should_throw);
3266  }
3267  // 2. Let newLenDesc be a copy of Desc.
3268  // (Actual copying is not necessary.)
3269  PropertyDescriptor* new_len_desc = desc;
3270  // 3. - 7. Convert Desc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3271  uint32_t new_len = 0;
3272  if (!AnythingToArrayLength(isolate, desc->value(), &new_len)) {
3273  DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
3274  return Nothing<bool>();
3275  }
3276  // 8. Set newLenDesc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3277  // (Done below, if needed.)
3278  // 9. Let oldLenDesc be OrdinaryGetOwnProperty(A, "length").
3279  PropertyDescriptor old_len_desc;
3280  Maybe<bool> success = GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
3281  isolate, a, isolate->factory()->length_string(), &old_len_desc);
3282  // 10. (Assert)
3283  DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3284  USE(success);
3285  // 11. Let oldLen be oldLenDesc.[[Value]].
3286  uint32_t old_len = 0;
3287  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*old_len_desc.value(), &old_len));
3288  // 12. If newLen >= oldLen, then
3289  if (new_len >= old_len) {
3290  // 8. Set newLenDesc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3291  // 12a. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", newLenDesc).
3292  new_len_desc->set_value(isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(new_len));
3293  return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, a,
3294  isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3295  new_len_desc, should_throw);
3296  }
3297  // 13. If oldLenDesc.[[Writable]] is false, return false.
3298  if (!old_len_desc.writable() ||
3299  // Also handle the {configurable: true} and enumerable changes
3300  // since we later use JSArray::SetLength instead of
3301  // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty to change the length,
3302  // and it doesn't have access to the descriptor anymore.
3303  new_len_desc->configurable() ||
3304  (new_len_desc->has_enumerable() &&
3305  (old_len_desc.enumerable() != new_len_desc->enumerable()))) {
3306  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3307  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
3308  isolate->factory()->length_string()));
3309  }
3310  // 14. If newLenDesc.[[Writable]] is absent or has the value true,
3311  // let newWritable be true.
3312  bool new_writable = false;
3313  if (!new_len_desc->has_writable() || new_len_desc->writable()) {
3314  new_writable = true;
3315  } else {
3316  // 15. Else,
3317  // 15a. Need to defer setting the [[Writable]] attribute to false in case
3318  // any elements cannot be deleted.
3319  // 15b. Let newWritable be false. (It's initialized as "false" anyway.)
3320  // 15c. Set newLenDesc.[[Writable]] to true.
3321  // (Not needed.)
3322  }
3323  // Most of steps 16 through 19 is implemented by JSArray::SetLength.
3324  MAYBE_RETURN(JSArray::SetLength(isolate, a, new_len), Nothing<bool>());
3325  // Steps 19d-ii, 20.
3326  if (!new_writable) {
3327  PropertyDescriptor readonly;
3328  readonly.set_writable(false);
3329  success = OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, a,
3330  isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3331  &readonly, should_throw);
3332  DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3333  USE(success);
3334  }
3335  uint32_t actual_new_len = 0;
3336  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(a->length(), &actual_new_len));
3337  // Steps 19d-v, 21. Return false if there were non-deletable elements.
3338  bool result = actual_new_len == new_len;
3339  if (!result) {
3340  RETURN_FAILURE(
3341  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3342  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictDeleteProperty,
3343  isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(actual_new_len - 1),
3344  a));
3345  }
3346  return Just(result);
3347 }
3348 
3349 // ES6 9.5.6
3350 // static
3351 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
3352  DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3353  DirectHandle<Object> key,
3354  PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3355  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3356  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3357  if (IsSymbol(*key) && Cast<Symbol>(key)->IsPrivate()) {
3358  DCHECK(!Cast<Symbol>(key)->IsPrivateName());
3359  return JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(isolate, proxy, Cast<Symbol>(key), desc,
3360  should_throw);
3361  }
3362  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = isolate->factory()->defineProperty_string();
3363  // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true.
3364  DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key));
3365  // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
3366  DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
3367  // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
3368  // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
3369  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3370  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3371  MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3372  return Nothing<bool>();
3373  }
3374  // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
3375  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3376  // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "defineProperty").
3377  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3378  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3379  isolate, trap,
3380  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
3381  Nothing<bool>());
3382  // 7. If trap is undefined, then:
3383  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3384  // 7a. Return target.[[DefineOwnProperty]](P, Desc).
3385  return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, target, key, desc,
3386  should_throw);
3387  }
3388  // 8. Let descObj be FromPropertyDescriptor(Desc).
3389  DirectHandle<Object> desc_obj = desc->ToObject(isolate);
3390  // 9. Let booleanTrapResult be
3391  // ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, target, P, descObj)).
3392  DirectHandle<Name> property_name =
3393  IsName(*key) ? Cast<Name>(key)
3394  : Cast<Name>(isolate->factory()->NumberToString(key));
3395  // Do not leak private property names.
3396  DCHECK(!property_name->IsPrivate());
3397  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result_obj;
3398  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, property_name, desc_obj};
3399  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3400  isolate, trap_result_obj,
3401  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3402  Nothing<bool>());
3403  // 10. If booleanTrapResult is false, return false.
3404  if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3405  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3406  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
3407  trap_name, property_name));
3408  }
3409  // 11. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3410  PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3411  Maybe<bool> target_found =
3412  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, key, &target_desc);
3413  MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
3414  // 12. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3415  Maybe<bool> maybe_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3416  MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_extensible, Nothing<bool>());
3417  bool extensible_target = maybe_extensible.FromJust();
3418  // 13. If Desc has a [[Configurable]] field and if Desc.[[Configurable]]
3419  // is false, then:
3420  // 13a. Let settingConfigFalse be true.
3421  // 14. Else let settingConfigFalse be false.
3422  bool setting_config_false = desc->has_configurable() && !desc->configurable();
3423  // 15. If targetDesc is undefined, then
3424  if (!target_found.FromJust()) {
3425  // 15a. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3426  if (!extensible_target) {
3427  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3428  MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonExtensible, property_name));
3429  return Nothing<bool>();
3430  }
3431  // 15b. If settingConfigFalse is true, throw a TypeError exception.
3432  if (setting_config_false) {
3433  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3434  MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurable, property_name));
3435  return Nothing<bool>();
3436  }
3437  } else {
3438  // 16. Else targetDesc is not undefined,
3439  // 16a. If IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(extensibleTarget, Desc,
3440  // targetDesc) is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3441  Maybe<bool> valid = IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
3442  isolate, extensible_target, desc, &target_desc, property_name,
3443  Just(kDontThrow));
3444  MAYBE_RETURN(valid, Nothing<bool>());
3445  if (!valid.FromJust()) {
3446  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3447  MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyIncompatible, property_name));
3448  return Nothing<bool>();
3449  }
3450  // 16b. If settingConfigFalse is true and targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
3451  // true, throw a TypeError exception.
3452  if (setting_config_false && target_desc.configurable()) {
3453  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3454  MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurable, property_name));
3455  return Nothing<bool>();
3456  }
3457  // 16c. If IsDataDescriptor(targetDesc) is true,
3458  // targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
3459  // false, and targetDesc.[[Writable]] is true, then
3460  if (PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
3461  !target_desc.configurable() && target_desc.writable()) {
3462  // 16c i. If Desc has a [[Writable]] field and Desc.[[Writable]] is false,
3463  // throw a TypeError exception.
3464  if (desc->has_writable() && !desc->writable()) {
3465  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3466  MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurableWritable,
3467  property_name));
3468  return Nothing<bool>();
3469  }
3470  }
3471  }
3472  // 17. Return true.
3473  return Just(true);
3474 }
3475 
3476 // static
3477 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(Isolate* isolate,
3478  DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3479  DirectHandle<Symbol> private_name,
3480  PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3481  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3482  // Despite the generic name, this can only add private data properties.
3483  if (!PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc) ||
3484  desc->ToAttributes() != DONT_ENUM) {
3485  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3486  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyPrivate));
3487  }
3488  DCHECK(proxy->map()->is_dictionary_map());
3489  DirectHandle<Object> value =
3490  desc->has_value() ? desc->value()
3491  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
3492 
3493  LookupIterator it(isolate, proxy, private_name, proxy);
3494 
3495  if (it.IsFound()) {
3496  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, it.state());
3497  DCHECK_EQ(DONT_ENUM, it.property_attributes());
3498  // We are not tracking constness for private symbols added to JSProxy
3499  // objects.
3500  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyConstness::kMutable, it.property_details().constness());
3501  it.WriteDataValue(value, false);
3502  return Just(true);
3503  }
3504 
3505  PropertyDetails details(PropertyKind::kData, DONT_ENUM,
3506  PropertyConstness::kMutable);
3507  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3508  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dict(proxy->property_dictionary_swiss(),
3509  isolate);
3510  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> result =
3511  SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, dict, private_name, value, details);
3512  if (!dict.is_identical_to(result)) proxy->SetProperties(*result);
3513  } else {
3514  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dict(proxy->property_dictionary(), isolate);
3515  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> result =
3516  NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dict, private_name, value, details);
3517  if (!dict.is_identical_to(result)) proxy->SetProperties(*result);
3518  }
3519  return Just(true);
3520 }

3522 // ES6 9.5.5
3523 // static
3524 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(Isolate* isolate,
3525  DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3526  DirectHandle<Name> name,
3527  PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
3528  DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
3529  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3530 
3531  DirectHandle<String> trap_name =
3532  isolate->factory()->getOwnPropertyDescriptor_string();
3533  // 1. (Assert)
3534  // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
3535  DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
3536  // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
3537  // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
3538  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3539  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3540  MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3541  return Nothing<bool>();
3542  }
3543  // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
3544  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3545  // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getOwnPropertyDescriptor").
3546  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3547  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3548  isolate, trap,
3549  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
3550  Nothing<bool>());
3551  // 7. If trap is undefined, then
3552  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3553  // 7a. Return target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3554  return JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, desc);
3555  }
3556  // 8. Let trapResultObj be ? Call(trap, handler, target, P).
3557  Handle<JSAny> trap_result_obj;
3558  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
3559  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3560  isolate, trap_result_obj,
3561  Cast<JSAny>(
3562  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args))),
3563  Nothing<bool>());
3564  // 9. If Type(trapResultObj) is neither Object nor Undefined, throw a
3565  // TypeError exception.
3566  if (!IsJSReceiver(*trap_result_obj) &&
3567  !IsUndefined(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3568  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3569  MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorInvalid, name));
3570  return Nothing<bool>();
3571  }
3572  // 10. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3573  PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3574  Maybe<bool> found =
3575  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
3576  MAYBE_RETURN(found, Nothing<bool>());
3577  // 11. If trapResultObj is undefined, then
3578  if (IsUndefined(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3579  // 11a. If targetDesc is undefined, return undefined.
3580  if (!found.FromJust()) return Just(false);
3581  // 11b. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError
3582  // exception.
3583  if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
3584  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3585  MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorUndefined, name));
3586  return Nothing<bool>();
3587  }
3588  // 11c. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3589  Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3590  MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3591  // 11d. (Assert)
3592  // 11e. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3593  if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
3594  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3595  MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonExtensible, name));
3596  return Nothing<bool>();
3597  }
3598  // 11f. Return undefined.
3599  return Just(false);
3600  }
3601  // 12. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3602  Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3603  MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3604  // 13. Let resultDesc be ? ToPropertyDescriptor(trapResultObj).
3605  if (!PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(isolate, trap_result_obj,
3606  desc)) {
3607  DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
3608  return Nothing<bool>();
3609  }
3610  // 14. Call CompletePropertyDescriptor(resultDesc).
3611  PropertyDescriptor::CompletePropertyDescriptor(isolate, desc);
3612  // 15. Let valid be IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor (extensibleTarget,
3613  // resultDesc, targetDesc).
3614  Maybe<bool> valid = IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
3615  isolate, extensible_target.FromJust(), desc, &target_desc, name,
3616  Just(kDontThrow));
3617  MAYBE_RETURN(valid, Nothing<bool>());
3618  // 16. If valid is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3619  if (!valid.FromJust()) {
3620  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3621  MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorIncompatible, name));
3622  return Nothing<bool>();
3623  }
3624  // 17. If resultDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, then
3625  if (!desc->configurable()) {
3626  // 17a. If targetDesc is undefined or targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is true:
3627  if (target_desc.is_empty() || target_desc.configurable()) {
3628  // 17a i. Throw a TypeError exception.
3629  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3630  MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonConfigurable,
3631  name));
3632  return Nothing<bool>();
3633  }
3634  // 17b. If resultDesc has a [[Writable]] field and resultDesc.[[Writable]]
3635  // is false, then
3636  if (desc->has_writable() && !desc->writable()) {
3637  // 17b i. If targetDesc.[[Writable]] is true, throw a TypeError exception.
3638  if (target_desc.writable()) {
3639  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3640  MessageTemplate::
3641  kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonConfigurableWritable,
3642  name));
3643  return Nothing<bool>();
3644  }
3645  }
3646  }
3647  // 18. Return resultDesc.
3648  return Just(true);
3649 }

3651 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::PreventExtensions(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3652  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
3653  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
3654  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3655  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3656  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->preventExtensions_string();
3657 
3658  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3659  isolate->Throw(
3660  *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3661  return Nothing<bool>();
3662  }
3663  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3664  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3665 
3666  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3667  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3668  isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3669  Nothing<bool>());
3670  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3671  return JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(isolate, target, should_throw);
3672  }
3673 
3674  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3675  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
3676  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3677  isolate, trap_result,
3678  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3679  Nothing<bool>());
3680  if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3681  RETURN_FAILURE(
3682  isolate, should_throw,
3683  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
3684  }
3685 
3686  // Enforce the invariant.
3687  Maybe<bool> target_result = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3688  MAYBE_RETURN(target_result, Nothing<bool>());
3689  if (target_result.FromJust()) {
3690  isolate->Throw(*factory->NewTypeError(
3691  MessageTemplate::kProxyPreventExtensionsExtensible));
3692  return Nothing<bool>();
3693  }
3694  return Just(true);
3695 }
3696 
3697 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::IsExtensible(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
3698  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
3699  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3700  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3701  DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->isExtensible_string();
3702 
3703  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3704  isolate->Throw(
3705  *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3706  return Nothing<bool>();
3707  }
3708  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3709  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3710 
3711  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3712  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3713  isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3714  Nothing<bool>());
3715  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3716  return JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3717  }
3718 
3719  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3720  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
3721  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3722  isolate, trap_result,
3723  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3724  Nothing<bool>());
3725 
3726  // Enforce the invariant.
3727  Maybe<bool> target_result = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3728  MAYBE_RETURN(target_result, Nothing<bool>());
3729  if (target_result.FromJust() != Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3730  isolate->Throw(
3731  *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyIsExtensibleInconsistent,
3732  factory->ToBoolean(target_result.FromJust())));
3733  return Nothing<bool>();
3734  }
3735  return target_result;
3736 }

3738 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::CopyUpTo(
3739  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> desc, int enumeration_index,
3740  int slack) {
3741  return DescriptorArray::CopyUpToAddAttributes(isolate, desc,
3742  enumeration_index, NONE, slack);
3743 }
3744 
3745 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::CopyUpToAddAttributes(
3746  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> source_handle,
3747  int enumeration_index, PropertyAttributes attributes, int slack) {
3748  if (enumeration_index + slack == 0) {
3749  return isolate->factory()->empty_descriptor_array();
3750  }
3751 
3752  int size = enumeration_index;
3753  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> copy_handle =
3754  DescriptorArray::Allocate(isolate, size, slack);
3755 
3756  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3757  Tagged<DescriptorArray> source = *source_handle;
3758  Tagged<DescriptorArray> copy = *copy_handle;
3759 
3760  if (attributes != NONE) {
3761  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(size)) {
3762  Tagged<MaybeObject> value_or_field_type = source->GetValue(i);
3763  Tagged<Name> key = source->GetKey(i);
3764  PropertyDetails details = source->GetDetails(i);
3765  // Bulk attribute changes never affect private properties.
3766  if (!key->IsPrivate()) {
3767  int mask = DONT_DELETE | DONT_ENUM;
3768  // READ_ONLY is an invalid attribute for JS setters/getters.
3769  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
3770  if (details.kind() != PropertyKind::kAccessor ||
3771  !(value_or_field_type.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object) &&
3772  IsAccessorPair(heap_object))) {
3773  mask |= READ_ONLY;
3774  }
3775  details = details.CopyAddAttributes(
3776  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(attributes & mask));
3777  }
3778  copy->Set(i, key, value_or_field_type, details);
3779  }
3780  } else {
3781  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(size)) {
3782  copy->CopyFrom(i, source);
3783  }
3784  }
3785 
3786  if (source->number_of_descriptors() != enumeration_index) copy->Sort();
3787 
3788  return copy_handle;
3789 }
3790 
3791 bool DescriptorArray::IsEqualUpTo(Tagged<DescriptorArray> desc,
3792  int nof_descriptors) {
3793  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(nof_descriptors)) {
3794  if (GetKey(i) != desc->GetKey(i) || GetValue(i) != desc->GetValue(i)) {
3795  return false;
3796  }
3797  PropertyDetails details = GetDetails(i);
3798  PropertyDetails other_details = desc->GetDetails(i);
3799  if (details.kind() != other_details.kind() ||
3800  details.location() != other_details.location() ||
3801  !details.representation().Equals(other_details.representation())) {
3802  return false;
3803  }
3804  }
3805  return true;
3806 }
3807 
3808 // static
3809 Handle<WeakArrayList> PrototypeUsers::Add(Isolate* isolate,
3810  Handle<WeakArrayList> array,
3811  DirectHandle<Map> value,
3812  int* assigned_index) {
3813  int length = array->length();
3814  if (length == 0) {
3815  // Uninitialized WeakArrayList; need to initialize empty_slot_index.
3816  array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(isolate, array, kFirstIndex + 1);
3817  set_empty_slot_index(*array, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3818  array->Set(kFirstIndex, MakeWeak(*value));
3819  array->set_length(kFirstIndex + 1);
3820  if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = kFirstIndex;
3821  return array;
3822  }
3823 
3824  // If the array has unfilled space at the end, use it.
3825  if (!array->IsFull()) {
3826  array->Set(length, MakeWeak(*value));
3827  array->set_length(length + 1);
3828  if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = length;
3829  return array;
3830  }
3831 
3832  // If there are empty slots, use one of them.
3833  int empty_slot = Smi::ToInt(empty_slot_index(*array));
3834 
3835  if (empty_slot == kNoEmptySlotsMarker) {
3836  // GCs might have cleared some references, rescan the array for empty slots.
3837  PrototypeUsers::ScanForEmptySlots(*array);
3838  empty_slot = Smi::ToInt(empty_slot_index(*array));
3839  }
3840 
3841  if (empty_slot != kNoEmptySlotsMarker) {
3842  DCHECK_GE(empty_slot, kFirstIndex);
3843  CHECK_LT(empty_slot, array->length());
3844  int next_empty_slot = array->Get(empty_slot).ToSmi().value();
3845 
3846  array->Set(empty_slot, MakeWeak(*value));
3847  if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = empty_slot;
3848 
3849  set_empty_slot_index(*array, next_empty_slot);
3850  return array;
3851  } else {
3852  DCHECK_EQ(empty_slot, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3853  }
3854 
3855  // Array full and no empty slots. Grow the array.
3856  array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(isolate, array, length + 1);
3857  array->Set(length, MakeWeak(*value));
3858  array->set_length(length + 1);
3859  if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = length;
3860  return array;
3861 }
3862 
3863 // static
3864 void PrototypeUsers::ScanForEmptySlots(Tagged<WeakArrayList> array) {
3865  for (int i = kFirstIndex; i < array->length(); i++) {
3866  if (array->Get(i).IsCleared()) {
3867  PrototypeUsers::MarkSlotEmpty(array, i);
3868  }
3869  }
3870 }
3871 
3872 Tagged<WeakArrayList> PrototypeUsers::Compact(DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> array,
3873  Heap* heap,
3874  CompactionCallback callback,
3875  AllocationType allocation) {
3876  if (array->length() == 0) {
3877  return *array;
3878  }
3879  int new_length = kFirstIndex + array->CountLiveWeakReferences();
3880  if (new_length == array->length()) {
3881  return *array;
3882  }
3883 
3884  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> new_array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(
3885  heap->isolate(),
3886  handle(ReadOnlyRoots(heap).empty_weak_array_list(), heap->isolate()),
3887  new_length, allocation);
3888  // Allocation might have caused GC and turned some of the elements into
3889  // cleared weak heap objects. Count the number of live objects again.
3890  int copy_to = kFirstIndex;
3891  for (int i = kFirstIndex; i < array->length(); i++) {
3892  Tagged<MaybeObject> element = array->Get(i);
3893  Tagged<HeapObject> value;
3894  if (element.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&value)) {
3895  callback(value, i, copy_to);
3896  new_array->Set(copy_to++, element);
3897  } else {
3898  DCHECK(element.IsCleared() || element.IsSmi());
3899  }
3900  }
3901  new_array->set_length(copy_to);
3902  set_empty_slot_index(*new_array, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3903  return *new_array;
3904 }
3905 
3906 template <typename IsolateT>
3907 Handle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::Allocate(IsolateT* isolate,
3908  int nof_descriptors,
3909  int slack,
3910  AllocationType allocation) {
3911  return nof_descriptors + slack == 0
3912  ? isolate->factory()->empty_descriptor_array()
3913  : isolate->factory()->NewDescriptorArray(nof_descriptors, slack,
3914  allocation);
3915 }
3916 template Handle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::Allocate(
3917  Isolate* isolate, int nof_descriptors, int slack,
3918  AllocationType allocation);
3919 template Handle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::Allocate(
3920  LocalIsolate* isolate, int nof_descriptors, int slack,
3921  AllocationType allocation);
3922 
3923 void DescriptorArray::Initialize(Tagged<EnumCache> empty_enum_cache,
3924  Tagged<HeapObject> undefined_value,
3925  int nof_descriptors, int slack,
3926  uint32_t raw_gc_state) {
3927  DCHECK_GE(nof_descriptors, 0);
3928  DCHECK_GE(slack, 0);
3929  DCHECK_LE(nof_descriptors + slack, kMaxNumberOfDescriptors);
3930  set_number_of_all_descriptors(nof_descriptors + slack);
3931  set_number_of_descriptors(nof_descriptors);
3932  set_raw_gc_state(raw_gc_state, kRelaxedStore);
3933  set_enum_cache(empty_enum_cache, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3934  set_flags(FastIterableBits::encode(FastIterableState::kUnknown),
3935  kRelaxedStore);
3936  MemsetTagged(GetDescriptorSlot(0), undefined_value,
3937  number_of_all_descriptors() * kEntrySize);
3938 }

3940 void DescriptorArray::ClearEnumCache() {

3973 void DescriptorArray::Sort() {
3974  // In-place heap sort.
3975  const int len = number_of_descriptors();
3976  // Reset sorting since the descriptor array might contain invalid pointers.
3977  for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i) SetSortedKey(i, i);
3978  // Bottom-up max-heap construction.
3979  // Index of the last node with children.
3980  int max_parent_index = (len / 2) - 1;
3981  for (int i = max_parent_index; i >= 0; --i) {
3982  int parent_index = i;
3983  const uint32_t parent_hash = GetSortedKey(i)->hash();
3984  while (parent_index <= max_parent_index) {
3985  int child_index = 2 * parent_index + 1;
3986  uint32_t child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index)->hash();
3987  if (child_index + 1 < len) {
3988  uint32_t right_child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index + 1)->hash();
3989  if (right_child_hash > child_hash) {
3990  child_index++;
3991  child_hash = right_child_hash;
3992  }
3993  }
3994  if (child_hash <= parent_hash) break;
3995  SwapSortedKeys(parent_index, child_index);
3996  // Now element at child_index could be < its children.
3997  parent_index = child_index; // parent_hash remains correct.
3998  }
3999  }
4000 
4001  // Extract elements and create sorted array.
4002  for (int i = len - 1; i > 0; --i) {
4003  // Put max element at the back of the array.
4004  SwapSortedKeys(0, i);
4005  // Shift down the new top element.
4006  int parent_index = 0;
4007  const uint32_t parent_hash = GetSortedKey(parent_index)->hash();
4008  max_parent_index = (i / 2) - 1;
4009  while (parent_index <= max_parent_index) {
4010  int child_index = parent_index * 2 + 1;
4011  uint32_t child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index)->hash();
4012  if (child_index + 1 < i) {
4013  uint32_t right_child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index + 1)->hash();
4014  if (right_child_hash > child_hash) {
4015  child_index++;
4016  child_hash = right_child_hash;
4017  }
4018  }
4019  if (child_hash <= parent_hash) break;
4020  SwapSortedKeys(parent_index, child_index);
4021  parent_index = child_index;
4022  }
4023  }
4024  DCHECK(IsSortedNoDuplicates());
4025 }
4026 
4027 void DescriptorArray::CheckNameCollisionDuringInsertion(Descriptor* desc,
4028  uint32_t desc_hash,
4029  int insertion_index) {
4030  DCHECK_GE(insertion_index, 0);
4031  DCHECK_LE(insertion_index, number_of_all_descriptors());
4032 
4033  if (insertion_index <= 0) return;
4034 
4035  for (int i = insertion_index; i > 0; --i) {
4036  Tagged<Name> current_key = GetSortedKey(i - 1);
4037  if (current_key->hash() != desc_hash) return;
4038  CHECK(current_key != *desc->GetKey());
4039  }
4040 }

4067  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();

4072 #ifdef DEBUG

4074  if (number_of_all_descriptors() != other->number_of_all_descriptors()) {
4075  return false;
4076  }

4078  if (GetKey(i) != other->GetKey(i)) return false;
4079  if (GetDetails(i).AsSmi() != other->GetDetails(i).AsSmi()) return false;
4080  if (GetValue(i) != other->GetValue(i)) return false;
4081  }
4082  return true;

4086 // static
4087 MaybeDirectHandle<String> Name::ToFunctionName(Isolate* isolate,
4088  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
4089  if (IsString(*name)) return Cast<String>(name);
4090  // ES6 section 9.2.11 SetFunctionName, step 4.
4091  DirectHandle<Object> description(Cast<Symbol>(name)->description(), isolate);
4092  if (IsUndefined(*description, isolate)) {
4093  return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4094  }
4095  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
4096  builder.AppendCharacter('[');
4097  builder.AppendString(Cast<String>(description));
4098  builder.AppendCharacter(']');
4099  return builder.Finish();
4100 }
