4158 namespace {
4159 
4160 template <typename sinkchar>
4161 void WriteFixedArrayToFlat(Tagged<FixedArray> fixed_array, int length,
4162  Tagged<String> separator, sinkchar* sink,
4163  int sink_length) {
4164  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4165  CHECK_GT(length, 0);
4166  CHECK_LE(length, fixed_array->length());
4167 #ifdef DEBUG
4168  sinkchar* sink_end = sink + sink_length;
4169 #endif
4170 
4171  const int separator_length = separator->length();
4172  const bool use_one_byte_separator_fast_path =
4173  separator_length == 1 && sizeof(sinkchar) == 1 &&
4174  StringShape(separator).IsSequentialOneByte();
4175  uint8_t separator_one_char;
4176  if (use_one_byte_separator_fast_path) {
4177  CHECK(StringShape(separator).IsSequentialOneByte());
4178  CHECK_EQ(separator->length(), 1);
4179  separator_one_char = Cast<SeqOneByteString>(separator)->GetChars(no_gc)[0];
4180  }
4181 
4182  uint32_t num_separators = 0;
4183  uint32_t repeat_last = 0;
4184  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4185  Tagged<Object> element = fixed_array->get(i);
4186  const bool element_is_special = IsSmi(element);
4187 
4188  // If element is a positive Smi, it represents the number of separators to
4189  // write. If it is a negative Smi, it represents the number of times the
4190  // last string is repeated.
4191  if (V8_UNLIKELY(element_is_special)) {
4192  int count;
4193  CHECK(Object::ToInt32(element, &count));
4194  if (count > 0) {
4195  num_separators = count;
4196  // Verify that Smis (number of separators) only occur when necessary:
4197  // 1) at the beginning
4198  // 2) at the end
4199  // 3) when the number of separators > 1
4200  // - It is assumed that consecutive Strings will have one
4201  // separator,
4202  // so there is no need for a Smi.
4203  DCHECK(i == 0 || i == length - 1 || num_separators > 1);
4204  } else {
4205  repeat_last = -count;
4206  // Repeat is only possible when the previous element is not special.
4207  DCHECK_GT(i, 0);
4208  DCHECK(IsString(fixed_array->get(i - 1)));
4209  }
4210  }
4211 
4212  // Write separator(s) if necessary.
4213  if (num_separators > 0 && separator_length > 0) {
4214  // TODO(pwong): Consider doubling strategy employed by runtime-strings.cc
4215  // WriteRepeatToFlat().
4216  // Fast path for single character, single byte separators.
4217  if (use_one_byte_separator_fast_path) {
4218  DCHECK_LE(sink + num_separators, sink_end);
4219  memset(sink, separator_one_char, num_separators);
4220  DCHECK_EQ(separator_length, 1);
4221  sink += num_separators;
4222  } else {
4223  for (uint32_t j = 0; j < num_separators; j++) {
4224  DCHECK_LE(sink + separator_length, sink_end);
4225  String::WriteToFlat(separator, sink, 0, separator_length);
4226  sink += separator_length;
4227  }
4228  }
4229  num_separators = 0;
4230  }
4231 
4232  // Repeat the last written string |repeat_last| times (including
4233  // separators).
4234  if (V8_UNLIKELY(repeat_last > 0)) {
4235  Tagged<Object> last_element = fixed_array->get(i - 1);
4236  int string_length = Cast<String>(last_element)->length();
4237  // The implemented logic requires that string length is > 0. Empty strings
4238  // are handled by repeating the separator (positive smi in the fixed
4239  // array) already.
4240  DCHECK_GT(string_length, 0);
4241  int length_with_sep = string_length + separator_length;
4242  // Only copy separators between elements, not at the start or beginning.
4243  sinkchar* copy_end =
4244  sink + (length_with_sep * repeat_last) - separator_length;
4245  int copy_length = length_with_sep;
4246  while (sink < copy_end - copy_length) {
4247  DCHECK_LE(sink + copy_length, sink_end);
4248  memcpy(sink, sink - copy_length, copy_length * sizeof(sinkchar));
4249  sink += copy_length;
4250  copy_length *= 2;
4251  }
4252  int remaining = static_cast<int>(copy_end - sink);
4253  if (remaining > 0) {
4254  DCHECK_LE(sink + remaining, sink_end);
4255  memcpy(sink, sink - remaining - separator_length,
4256  remaining * sizeof(sinkchar));
4257  sink += remaining;
4258  }
4259  repeat_last = 0;
4260  num_separators = 1;
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (V8_LIKELY(!element_is_special)) {
4264  DCHECK(IsString(element));
4265  Tagged<String> string = Cast<String>(element);
4266  const int string_length = string->length();
4267 
4268  DCHECK(string_length == 0 || sink < sink_end);
4269  String::WriteToFlat(string, sink, 0, string_length);
4270  sink += string_length;
4271 
4272  // Next string element, needs at least one separator preceding it.
4273  num_separators = 1;
4274  }
4275  }
4276 
4277  // Verify we have written to the end of the sink.
4278  DCHECK_EQ(sink, sink_end);
4279 }
4280 
4281 } // namespace

4283 // static
4284 Address JSArray::ArrayJoinConcatToSequentialString(Isolate* isolate,
4285  Address raw_fixed_array,
4286  intptr_t length,
4287  Address raw_separator,
4288  Address raw_dest) {
4289  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4290  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
4291  Tagged<FixedArray> fixed_array =
4292  Cast<FixedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_fixed_array));
4293  Tagged<String> separator = Cast<String>(Tagged<Object>(raw_separator));
4294  Tagged<String> dest = Cast<String>(Tagged<Object>(raw_dest));
4295  DCHECK(IsFixedArray(fixed_array));
4296  DCHECK(StringShape(dest).IsSequentialOneByte() ||
4297  StringShape(dest).IsSequentialTwoByte());
4298 
4299  if (StringShape(dest).IsSequentialOneByte()) {
4300  WriteFixedArrayToFlat(fixed_array, static_cast<int>(length), separator,
4301  Cast<SeqOneByteString>(dest)->GetChars(no_gc),
4302  dest->length());
4303  } else {
4304  DCHECK(StringShape(dest).IsSequentialTwoByte());
4305  WriteFixedArrayToFlat(fixed_array, static_cast<int>(length), separator,
4306  Cast<SeqTwoByteString>(dest)->GetChars(no_gc),
4307  dest->length());
4308  }
4309  return dest.ptr();
4310 }

4331 // static
4332 int Script::GetEvalPosition(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script) {
4333  DCHECK(script->compilation_type() == Script::CompilationType::kEval);
4334  int position = script->eval_from_position();
4335  if (position < 0) {
4336  // Due to laziness, the position may not have been translated from code
4337  // offset yet, which would be encoded as negative integer. In that case,
4338  // translate and set the position.
4339  if (!script->has_eval_from_shared()) {
4340  position = 0;
4341  } else {
4342  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(script->eval_from_shared(),
4343  isolate);
4344  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared);
4345  position =
4346  shared->abstract_code(isolate)->SourcePosition(isolate, -position);
4347  }
4348  DCHECK_GE(position, 0);
4349  script->set_eval_from_position(position);
4350  }
4351  return position;
4352 }

4452 void Script::TraceScriptRundown() {
4453  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4454  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4455  Tagged<Object> context_value = isolate->native_context()->debug_context_id();
4456  int contextId = (IsSmi(context_value)) ? Smi::ToInt(context_value) : 0;
4457  auto value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4458  value->SetInteger("scriptId", this->id());
4459  value->SetInteger("executionContextId", contextId);
4460  value->SetUnsignedInteger("isolate", isolate->debug()->IsolateId());
4461  value->SetBoolean("isModule", this->origin_options().IsModule());
4462  value->SetBoolean("hasSourceUrl", this->HasSourceURLComment());
4463  if (this->HasValidSource()) {
4464  if (this->HasSourceURLComment()) {
4465  value->SetString("sourceUrl",
4466  Cast<String>(this->source_url())->ToCString().get());
4467  }
4468  if (this->HasSourceMappingURLComment()) {
4469  Tagged<String> sourceMapUrl = Cast<String>(this->source_mapping_url());
4470  // Source maps can be huge. Don't ever put a huge data url source map in
4471  // the trace. Also omit unusually large regular URLs.
4472  constexpr int kMaxSourceMapUrlLength = 2048;
4473  if (sourceMapUrl->length() > kMaxSourceMapUrlLength) {
4474  // Signal that there is a source map - clients may wish to request it by
4475  // other means (such as via CDP) or otherwise warn that a source map was
4476  // present but elided.
4477  value->SetBoolean("sourceMapUrlElided", true);
4478  } else {
4479  value->SetString("sourceMapUrl", sourceMapUrl->ToCString().get());
4480  }
4481  }
4482  }
4483  if (IsString(this->name())) {
4484  value->SetString("url", Cast<String>(this->name())->ToCString().get());
4485  }
4486  TRACE_EVENT1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown"),
4487  "ScriptCatchup", "data", std::move(value));
4488 }
4489 
4490 void Script::TraceScriptRundownSources() {
4491  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4492  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4493  if (!IsString(this->source())) return;
4494  Tagged<String> source = Cast<String>(this->source());
4495  auto script_id = this->id();
4496  int32_t source_length = source->length();
4497 
4498  const int32_t kSourceMaxLength = 25000000; // 25mb
4499  const int32_t kSplitMaxLength = 1000000; // 1mb
4500  if (source_length > kSourceMaxLength) {
4501  auto value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4502  value->SetUnsignedInteger("isolate", isolate->debug()->IsolateId());
4503  value->SetInteger("scriptId", script_id);
4504  value->SetInteger("length", source_length);
4505  value->SetInteger("limit", kSourceMaxLength);
4506  TRACE_EVENT1(
4507  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4508  "TooLargeScriptCatchup", "data", std::move(value));
4509  } else if (source_length <= kSplitMaxLength) {
4510  auto value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4511  value->SetUnsignedInteger("isolate", isolate->debug()->IsolateId());
4512  value->SetInteger("scriptId", script_id);
4513  value->SetInteger("length", source_length);
4514  value->SetString("sourceText", source->ToCString().get());
4515  TRACE_EVENT1(
4516  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4517  "ScriptCatchup", "data", std::move(value));
4518  } else {
4519  int32_t split_count = source_length / kSplitMaxLength + 1;
4520  std::unique_ptr<char[]> source_ptr = source->ToCString();
4521  for (int32_t i = 0; i < split_count; i++) {
4522  int32_t begin = i * kSplitMaxLength;
4523  int32_t end = std::min(begin + kSplitMaxLength, source_length);
4524  auto split_trace_value = v8::tracing::TracedValue::Create();
4525  split_trace_value->SetInteger("splitIndex", i);
4526  split_trace_value->SetInteger("splitCount", split_count);
4527  split_trace_value->SetUnsignedInteger("isolate",
4528  isolate->debug()->IsolateId());
4529  split_trace_value->SetInteger("scriptId", script_id);
4530  split_trace_value->SetString(
4531  "sourceText", std::string(source_ptr.get() + begin, end - begin));
4532  TRACE_EVENT1(
4533  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4534  "LargeScriptCatchup", "data", std::move(split_trace_value));
4535  }
4536  }
4537 }

4541 template <typename Char>
4542 bool GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(base::Vector<Char> source, int position,
4543  Script::PositionInfo* info) {
4544  DCHECK(DisallowPositionInfoSlow::IsAllowed());
4545  if (position < 0) {
4546  position = 0;
4547  }
4548  int line = 0;
4549  const auto begin = std::cbegin(source);
4550  const auto end = std::cend(source);
4551  for (auto line_begin = begin; line_begin < end;) {
4552  const auto line_end = std::find(line_begin, end, '\n');
4553  if (position <= (line_end - begin)) {
4554  info->line = line;
4555  info->column = static_cast<int>((begin + position) - line_begin);
4556  info->line_start = static_cast<int>(line_begin - begin);
4557  info->line_end = static_cast<int>(line_end - begin);
4558  return true;
4559  }
4560  ++line;
4561  line_begin = line_end + 1;
4562  }
4563  return false;
4564 }
4565 bool GetPositionInfoSlow(const Tagged<Script> script, int position,
4566  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc,
4567  Script::PositionInfo* info) {
4568  if (!IsString(script->source())) {
4569  return false;
4570  }
4571  auto source = Cast<String>(script->source());
4572  const auto flat = source->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
4573  return flat.IsOneByte()
4574  ? GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(flat.ToOneByteVector(), position, info)
4575  : GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(flat.ToUC16Vector(), position, info);
4576 }

4592 template <typename LineEndsContainer>
4593 bool GetLineEndsContainerPositionInfo(const LineEndsContainer& ends,
4594  int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4595  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
4596  const int ends_len = GetLength(ends);
4597  if (ends_len == 0) return false;
4598 
4599  // Return early on invalid positions. Negative positions behave as if 0 was
4600  // passed, and positions beyond the end of the script return as failure.
4601  if (position < 0) {
4602  position = 0;
4603  } else if (position > GetLineEnd(ends, ends_len - 1)) {
4604  return false;
4605  }
4606 
4607  // Determine line number by doing a binary search on the line ends array.
4608  if (GetLineEnd(ends, 0) >= position) {
4609  info->line = 0;
4610  info->line_start = 0;
4611  info->column = position;
4612  } else {
4613  int left = 0;
4614  int right = ends_len - 1;
4615 
4616  while (right > 0) {
4617  DCHECK_LE(left, right);
4618  const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
4619  if (position > GetLineEnd(ends, mid)) {
4620  left = mid + 1;
4621  } else if (position <= GetLineEnd(ends, mid - 1)) {
4622  right = mid - 1;
4623  } else {
4624  info->line = mid;
4625  break;
4626  }
4627  }
4628  DCHECK(GetLineEnd(ends, info->line) >= position &&
4629  GetLineEnd(ends, info->line - 1) < position);
4630  info->line_start = GetLineEnd(ends, info->line - 1) + 1;
4631  info->column = position - info->line_start;
4632  }
4633 
4634  return true;
4635 }
4636 
4637 } // namespace
4638 
4639 void Script::AddPositionInfoOffset(PositionInfo* info,
4640  OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4641  // Add offsets if requested.
4642  if (offset_flag == OffsetFlag::kWithOffset) {
4643  if (info->line == 0) {
4644  info->column += column_offset();
4645  }
4646  info->line += line_offset();
4647  } else {
4648  DCHECK_EQ(offset_flag, OffsetFlag::kNoOffset);
4649  }
4650 }
4651 
4652 template <typename LineEndsContainer>
4653 bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal(
4654  const LineEndsContainer& ends, int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4655  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const {
4656  if (!GetLineEndsContainerPositionInfo(ends, position, info, no_gc))
4657  return false;
4658 
4659  // Line end is position of the linebreak character.
4660  info->line_end = GetLineEnd(ends, info->line);
4661  if (info->line_end > 0) {
4662  DCHECK(IsString(source()));
4663  Tagged<String> src = Cast<String>(source());
4664  if (src->length() >= static_cast<uint32_t>(info->line_end) &&
4665  src->Get(info->line_end - 1) == '\r') {
4666  info->line_end--;
4667  }
4668  }
4669 
4670  return true;
4671 }
4672 
4673 template bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal<String::LineEndsVector>(
4674  const String::LineEndsVector& ends, int position,
4675  Script::PositionInfo* info, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const;
4676 template bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal<Tagged<FixedArray>>(
4677  const Tagged<FixedArray>& ends, int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4678  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const;
4679 
4680 bool Script::GetPositionInfo(int position, PositionInfo* info,
4681  OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4682  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4683 
4684 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4685  // For wasm, we use the byte offset as the column.
4686  if (type() == Script::Type::kWasm) {
4687  DCHECK_LE(0, position);
4688  wasm::NativeModule* native_module = wasm_native_module();
4689  const wasm::WasmModule* module = native_module->module();
4690  if (module->functions.empty()) return false;
4691  info->line = 0;
4692  info->column = position;
4693  info->line_start = module->functions[0].code.offset();
4694  info->line_end = module->functions.back().code.end_offset();
4695  return true;
4696  }
4697 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4698 
4699  if (!has_line_ends()) {
4700  // Slow mode: we do not have line_ends. We have to iterate through source.
4701  if (!GetPositionInfoSlow(*this, position, no_gc, info)) {
4702  return false;
4703  }
4704  } else {
4705  DCHECK(has_line_ends());
4706  Tagged<FixedArray> ends = Cast<FixedArray>(line_ends());
4707 
4708  if (!GetPositionInfoInternal(ends, position, info, no_gc)) return false;
4709  }
4710 
4711  AddPositionInfoOffset(info, offset_flag);
4712 
4713  return true;
4714 }
4715 
4716 bool Script::GetPositionInfoWithLineEnds(
4717  int position, PositionInfo* info, const String::LineEndsVector& line_ends,
4718  OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4719  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4720  if (!GetPositionInfoInternal(line_ends, position, info, no_gc)) return false;
4721 
4722  AddPositionInfoOffset(info, offset_flag);
4723 
4724  return true;
4725 }

4727 bool Script::GetLineColumnWithLineEnds(

4733  line = -1;
4734  column = -1;
4735  return false;
4736  }
4737 
4738  line = info.line;
4739  column = info.column;
4740 
4741  return true;
4742 }

4774 // static
4775 DirectHandle<String> Script::GetScriptHash(Isolate* isolate,
4776  DirectHandle<Script> script,
4777  bool forceForInspector) {
4778  if (script->origin_options().IsOpaque() && !forceForInspector) {
4779  return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4780  }
4781 
4782  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
4783  {
4784  Tagged<Object> maybe_source_hash = script->source_hash(cage_base);
4785  if (IsString(maybe_source_hash, cage_base)) {
4786  DirectHandle<String> precomputed(Cast<String>(maybe_source_hash),
4787  isolate);
4788  if (precomputed->length() > 0) {
4789  return precomputed;
4790  }
4791  }
4792  }
4793 
4794  DirectHandle<String> src_text;
4795  {
4796  Tagged<Object> maybe_script_source = script->source(cage_base);
4797 
4798  if (!IsString(maybe_script_source, cage_base)) {
4799  return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4800  }
4801  src_text = direct_handle(Cast<String>(maybe_script_source), isolate);
4802  }
4803 
4804  char formatted_hash[kSizeOfFormattedSha256Digest];
4805 
4806  std::unique_ptr<char[]> string_val = src_text->ToCString();
4807  size_t len = strlen(string_val.get());
4808  uint8_t hash[kSizeOfSha256Digest];
4809  SHA256_hash(string_val.get(), len, hash);
4810  FormatBytesToHex(formatted_hash, kSizeOfFormattedSha256Digest, hash,
4811  kSizeOfSha256Digest);
4812  formatted_hash[kSizeOfSha256Digest * 2] = '\0';
4813 
4814  DirectHandle<String> result =
4815  isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(formatted_hash);
4816  script->set_source_hash(*result);
4817  return result;
4818 }

4820 template <typename IsolateT>
4821 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(
4822  DirectHandle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate,
4823  FunctionLiteral* function_literal) {
4824  DCHECK(function_literal->shared_function_info().is_null());
4825  int function_literal_id = function_literal->function_literal_id();
4826  CHECK_NE(function_literal_id, kInvalidInfoId);
4827  // If this check fails, the problem is most probably the function id
4828  // renumbering done by AstFunctionLiteralIdReindexer; in particular, that
4829  // AstTraversalVisitor doesn't recurse properly in the construct which
4830  // triggers the mismatch.
4831  CHECK_LT(function_literal_id, script->infos()->length());
4832  Tagged<MaybeObject> shared = script->infos()->get(function_literal_id);
4833  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
4834  if (!shared.GetHeapObject(&heap_object) ||
4835  IsUndefined(heap_object, isolate)) {
4836  return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
4837  }
4838  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> result(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(heap_object),
4839  isolate);
4840  function_literal->set_shared_function_info(result);
4841  return result;
4842 }

4844  DirectHandle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate,
4845  FunctionLiteral* function_literal);

4847  DirectHandle<Script> script, LocalIsolate* isolate,
4848  FunctionLiteral* function_literal);

4878 // ES6: 9.5.2 [[SetPrototypeOf]] (V)
4879 // static
4880 Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
4881  DirectHandle<Object> value,
4882  bool from_javascript,
4883  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4884  STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
4885  DirectHandle<Name> trap_name = isolate->factory()->setPrototypeOf_string();
4886  // 1. Assert: Either Type(V) is Object or Type(V) is Null.
4887  DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*value) || IsNull(*value, isolate));
4888  // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
4889  DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
4890  // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
4891  // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
4892  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
4893  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4894  MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
4895  return Nothing<bool>();
4896  }
4897  // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot.
4898  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
4899  // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getPrototypeOf").
4900  DirectHandle<Object> trap;
4901  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4902  isolate, trap,
4903  Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
4904  Nothing<bool>());
4905  // 7. If trap is undefined, then return target.[[SetPrototypeOf]]().
4906  if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
4907  return JSReceiver::SetPrototype(isolate, target, value, from_javascript,
4908  should_throw);
4909  }
4910  // 8. Let booleanTrapResult be ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, target, V)).
4911  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, value};
4912  DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
4913  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4914  isolate, trap_result,
4915  Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
4916  Nothing<bool>());
4917  bool bool_trap_result = Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate);
4918  // 9. If booleanTrapResult is false, return false.
4919  if (!bool_trap_result) {
4920  RETURN_FAILURE(
4921  isolate, should_throw,
4922  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
4923  }
4924  // 10. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
4925  Maybe<bool> is_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
4926  if (is_extensible.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
4927  // 11. If extensibleTarget is true, return true.
4928  if (is_extensible.FromJust()) {
4929  if (bool_trap_result) return Just(true);
4930  RETURN_FAILURE(
4931  isolate, should_throw,
4932  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
4933  }
4934  // 12. Let targetProto be ? target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
4935  DirectHandle<Object> target_proto;
4936  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, target_proto,
4937  JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target),
4938  Nothing<bool>());
4939  // 13. If SameValue(V, targetProto) is false, throw a TypeError exception.
4940  if (bool_trap_result && !Object::SameValue(*value, *target_proto)) {
4941  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4942  MessageTemplate::kProxySetPrototypeOfNonExtensible));
4943  return Nothing<bool>();
4944  }
4945  // 14. Return true.
4946  return Just(true);
4947 }

4971 bool AllocationSite::IsNested() {
4972  DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_track_allocation_sites);
4973  Tagged<Object> current = Isolate::Current()->heap()->allocation_sites_list();
4974  while (IsAllocationSite(current)) {
4975  Tagged<AllocationSiteWithWeakNext> current_site =
4976  Cast<AllocationSiteWithWeakNext>(current);
4977  if (current_site->nested_site() == this) {
4978  return true;
4979  }
4980  current = current_site->weak_next();
4981  }
4982  return false;
4983 }

5048 // static
5049 Handle<Object> JSPromise::Fulfill(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
5050  DirectHandle<Object> value) {
5051  Isolate* const isolate = Isolate::Current();
5052 
5053 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
5054  if (isolate->HasContextPromiseHooks()) {
5055  isolate->raw_native_context()->RunPromiseHook(
5056  PromiseHookType::kResolve, indirect_handle(promise, isolate),
5057  isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
5058  }
5059 #endif
5060 
5061  // 1. Assert: The value of promise.[[PromiseState]] is "pending".
5062  CHECK_EQ(Promise::kPending, promise->status());
5063 
5064  // 2. Let reactions be promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]].
5065  DirectHandle<Object> reactions(promise->reactions(), isolate);
5066 
5067  // 3. Set promise.[[PromiseResult]] to value.
5068  // 4. Set promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]] to undefined.
5069  // 5. Set promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]] to undefined.
5070  promise->set_reactions_or_result(Cast<JSAny>(*value));
5071 
5072  // 6. Set promise.[[PromiseState]] to "fulfilled".
5073  promise->set_status(Promise::kFulfilled);
5074 
5075  // 7. Return TriggerPromiseReactions(reactions, value).
5076  return TriggerPromiseReactions(isolate, reactions, value,
5077  PromiseReaction::kFulfill);
5078 }
5079 
5080 static void MoveMessageToPromise(Isolate* isolate,
5081  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
5082  if (!isolate->has_pending_message()) return;
5083 
5084  if (isolate->debug()->is_active()) {
5085  DirectHandle<Object> message(isolate->pending_message(), isolate);
5086  DirectHandle<Symbol> key =
5087  isolate->factory()->promise_debug_message_symbol();
5088  Object::SetProperty(isolate, promise, key, message,
5089  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
5090  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
5091  .Assert();
5092  }
5093 
5094  // The message object for a rejected promise was only stored for this purpose.
5095  // Clear it, otherwise we might leak memory.
5096  isolate->clear_pending_message();
5097 }
5098 
5099 // static
5100 Handle<Object> JSPromise::Reject(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
5101  DirectHandle<Object> reason,
5102  bool debug_event) {
5103  Isolate* const isolate = Isolate::Current();
5104  DCHECK(
5105  !reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate)->GetCurrentContext().IsEmpty());
5106 
5107  MoveMessageToPromise(isolate, promise);
5108 
5109  if (debug_event) isolate->debug()->OnPromiseReject(promise, reason);
5110  isolate->RunAllPromiseHooks(PromiseHookType::kResolve, promise,
5111  isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
5112 
5113  // 1. Assert: The value of promise.[[PromiseState]] is "pending".
5114  CHECK_EQ(Promise::kPending, promise->status());
5115 
5116  // 2. Let reactions be promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]].
5117  DirectHandle<Object> reactions(promise->reactions(), isolate);
5118 
5119  // 3. Set promise.[[PromiseResult]] to reason.
5120  // 4. Set promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]] to undefined.
5121  // 5. Set promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]] to undefined.
5122  promise->set_reactions_or_result(Cast<JSAny>(*reason));
5123 
5124  // 6. Set promise.[[PromiseState]] to "rejected".
5125  promise->set_status(Promise::kRejected);
5126 
5127  // 7. If promise.[[PromiseIsHandled]] is false, perform
5128  // HostPromiseRejectionTracker(promise, "reject").
5129  if (!promise->has_handler()) {
5130  isolate->ReportPromiseReject(promise, reason, kPromiseRejectWithNoHandler);
5131  }
5132 
5133  // 8. Return TriggerPromiseReactions(reactions, reason).
5134  return TriggerPromiseReactions(isolate, reactions, reason,
5135  PromiseReaction::kReject);
5136 }
5137 
5138 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-promise-resolve-functions
5139 // static
5140 MaybeHandle<Object> JSPromise::Resolve(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
5141  DirectHandle<Object> resolution_obj) {
5142  Isolate* const isolate = Isolate::Current();
5143  DCHECK(
5144  !reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate)->GetCurrentContext().IsEmpty());
5145 
5146  isolate->RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kResolve, promise,
5147  isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
5148 
5149  // 7. If SameValue(resolution, promise) is true, then
5150  if (promise.is_identical_to(resolution_obj)) {
5151  // a. Let selfResolutionError be a newly created TypeError object.
5152  DirectHandle<Object> self_resolution_error =
5153  isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kPromiseCyclic,
5154  resolution_obj);
5155  // b. Return RejectPromise(promise, selfResolutionError).
5156  return Reject(promise, self_resolution_error);
5157  }
5158 
5159  // 8. If Type(resolution) is not Object, then
5160  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> resolution_recv;
5161  if (!TryCast<JSReceiver>(resolution_obj, &resolution_recv)) {
5162  // a. Return FulfillPromise(promise, resolution).
5163  return Fulfill(promise, resolution_obj);
5164  }
5165 
5166  // 9. Let then be Get(resolution, "then").
5167  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> then;
5168 
5169  // Make sure a lookup of "then" on any JSPromise whose [[Prototype]] is the
5170  // initial %PromisePrototype% yields the initial method. In addition this
5171  // protector also guards the negative lookup of "then" on the intrinsic
5172  // %ObjectPrototype%, meaning that such lookups are guaranteed to yield
5173  // undefined without triggering any side-effects.
5174  if (IsJSPromise(*resolution_recv) &&
5175  resolution_recv->map()->prototype()->map()->instance_type() ==
5176  JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE &&
5177  Protectors::IsPromiseThenLookupChainIntact(isolate)) {
5178  // We can skip the "then" lookup on {resolution} if its [[Prototype]]
5179  // is the (initial) Promise.prototype and the Promise#then protector
5180  // is intact, as that guards the lookup path for the "then" property
5181  // on JSPromise instances which have the (initial) %PromisePrototype%.
5182  then = isolate->promise_then();
5183  } else {
5184  then = JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, resolution_recv,
5185  isolate->factory()->then_string());
5186  }
5187 
5188  // 10. If then is an abrupt completion, then
5189  DirectHandle<Object> then_action;
5190  if (!then.ToHandle(&then_action)) {
5191  // The "then" lookup can cause termination.
5192  if (!isolate->is_catchable_by_javascript(isolate->exception())) {
5193  return kNullMaybeHandle;
5194  }
5195 
5196  // a. Return RejectPromise(promise, then.[[Value]]).
5197  DirectHandle<Object> reason(isolate->exception(), isolate);
5198  isolate->clear_exception();
5199  return Reject(promise, reason, false);
5200  }
5201 
5202  // 11. Let thenAction be then.[[Value]].
5203  // 12. If IsCallable(thenAction) is false, then
5204  if (!IsCallable(*then_action)) {
5205  // a. Return FulfillPromise(promise, resolution).
5206  return Fulfill(promise, resolution_recv);
5207  }
5208 
5209  // 13. Let job be NewPromiseResolveThenableJob(promise, resolution,
5210  // thenAction).
5211  DirectHandle<NativeContext> then_context;
5212  if (!JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(Cast<JSReceiver>(then_action))
5213  .ToHandle(&then_context)) {
5214  then_context = isolate->native_context();
5215  }
5216 
5217  DirectHandle<PromiseResolveThenableJobTask> task =
5218  isolate->factory()->NewPromiseResolveThenableJobTask(
5219  promise, resolution_recv, Cast<JSReceiver>(then_action),
5220  then_context);
5221  if (isolate->debug()->is_active() && IsJSPromise(*resolution_recv)) {
5222  // Mark the dependency of the new {promise} on the {resolution}.
5223  Object::SetProperty(isolate, resolution_recv,
5224  isolate->factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol(),
5225  promise)
5226  .Check();
5227  }
5228  MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue = then_context->microtask_queue();
5229  if (microtask_queue) microtask_queue->EnqueueMicrotask(*task);
5230 
5231  // 15. Return undefined.
5232  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
5233 }
5234 
5235 // static
5236 Handle<Object> JSPromise::TriggerPromiseReactions(
5237  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> reactions,
5238  DirectHandle<Object> argument, PromiseReaction::Type type) {
5239  CHECK(IsSmi(*reactions) || IsPromiseReaction(*reactions));
5240 
5241  // We need to reverse the {reactions} here, since we record them
5242  // on the JSPromise in the reverse order.
5243  {
5244  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5245  Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> current =
5246  Cast<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>>(*reactions);
5247  Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> reversed = Smi::zero();
5248  while (!IsSmi(current)) {
5249  Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> next =
5250  Cast<PromiseReaction>(current)->next();
5251  Cast<PromiseReaction>(current)->set_next(reversed);
5252  reversed = current;
5253  current = next;
5254  }
5255  reactions = direct_handle(reversed, isolate);
5256  }
5257 
5258  // Morph the {reactions} into PromiseReactionJobTasks
5259  // and push them onto the microtask queue.
5260  while (!IsSmi(*reactions)) {
5261  auto task = Cast<HeapObject>(reactions);
5262  auto reaction = Cast<PromiseReaction>(task);
5263  reactions = direct_handle(reaction->next(), isolate);
5264 
5265  // According to HTML, we use the context of the appropriate handler as the
5266  // context of the microtask. See step 3 of HTML's EnqueueJob:
5267  // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/C/#enqueuejob(queuename,-job,-arguments)
5268  DirectHandle<NativeContext> handler_context;
5269 
5270  DirectHandle<UnionOf<Undefined, JSCallable>> primary_handler;
5271  DirectHandle<UnionOf<Undefined, JSCallable>> secondary_handler;
5272  if (type == PromiseReaction::kFulfill) {
5273  primary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate);
5274  secondary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate);
5275  } else {
5276  primary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate);
5277  secondary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate);
5278  }
5279 
5280  bool has_handler_context = false;
5281  if (IsJSReceiver(*primary_handler)) {
5282  has_handler_context =
5283  JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(Cast<JSReceiver>(primary_handler))
5284  .ToHandle(&handler_context);
5285  }
5286  if (!has_handler_context && IsJSReceiver(*secondary_handler)) {
5287  has_handler_context = JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(
5288  Cast<JSReceiver>(secondary_handler))
5289  .ToHandle(&handler_context);
5290  }
5291  if (!has_handler_context) handler_context = isolate->native_context();
5292 
5293  static_assert(
5294  static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kSize) ==
5295  static_cast<int>(
5296  PromiseReactionJobTask::kSizeOfAllPromiseReactionJobTasks));
5297  if (type == PromiseReaction::kFulfill) {
5298  task->set_map(
5299  isolate,
5300  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).promise_fulfill_reaction_job_task_map(),
5301  kReleaseStore);
5302  Cast<PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask>(task)->set_argument(*argument);
5303  Cast<PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask>(task)->set_context(*handler_context);
5304  static_assert(
5305  static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kFulfillHandlerOffset) ==
5306  static_cast<int>(PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::kHandlerOffset));
5307  static_assert(
5308  static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset) ==
5309  static_cast<int>(
5310  PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset));
5311 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5312  static_assert(
5313  static_cast<int>(
5314  PromiseReaction::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset) ==
5315  static_cast<int>(PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::
5316  kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset));
5317 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5318  } else {
5319  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5320  task->set_map(
5321  isolate,
5322  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).promise_reject_reaction_job_task_map(),
5323  kReleaseStore);
5324  Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_argument(*argument);
5325  Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_context(*handler_context);
5326  Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_handler(*primary_handler);
5327  static_assert(
5328  static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset) ==
5329  static_cast<int>(
5330  PromiseRejectReactionJobTask::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset));
5331 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5332  static_assert(
5333  static_cast<int>(
5334  PromiseReaction::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset) ==
5335  static_cast<int>(PromiseRejectReactionJobTask::
5336  kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset));
5337 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5338  }
5339 
5340  MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue = handler_context->microtask_queue();
5341  if (microtask_queue) {
5342  microtask_queue->EnqueueMicrotask(*Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(task));
5343  }
5344  }
5345 
5346  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
5347 }

5350 const uint32_t EphemeronHashTableShape::kHashBits = 10;
5351 #else
5352 const uint32_t EphemeronHashTableShape::kHashBits =
5353  PropertyArray::HashField::kSize;
5354 #endif // V8_LOWER_LIMITS_MODE

5367 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5368 template <typename IsolateT>
5369 Handle<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::New(
5370  IsolateT* isolate, int at_least_space_for, AllocationType allocation,
5371  MinimumCapacity capacity_option) {
5372  DCHECK_LE(0, at_least_space_for);
5373  DCHECK_IMPLIES(capacity_option == USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY,
5374  base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(at_least_space_for));
5375 
5376  uint32_t capacity = (capacity_option == USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY)
5377  ? at_least_space_for
5378  : ComputeCapacity(at_least_space_for);
5379  if (capacity > HashTable::kMaxCapacity) {
5380  isolate->FatalProcessOutOfHeapMemory("invalid table size");
5381  }
5382  return NewInternal(isolate, capacity, allocation);
5383 }
5384 
5385 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5386 template <typename IsolateT>
5387 Handle<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::NewInternal(
5388  IsolateT* isolate, int capacity, AllocationType allocation) {
5389  auto* factory = isolate->factory();
5390  int length = EntryToIndex(InternalIndex(capacity));
5391  Handle<FixedArray> array = factory->NewFixedArrayWithMap(
5392  Derived::GetMap(isolate->roots_table()), length, allocation);
5393  Handle<Derived> table = Cast<Derived>(array);
5394  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5395  Tagged<Derived> raw_table = *table;
5396  raw_table->SetNumberOfElements(0);
5397  raw_table->SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5398  raw_table->SetCapacity(capacity);
5399  return table;
5400 }
5401 
5402 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5403 void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Rehash(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
5404  Tagged<Derived> new_table) {
5405  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5406  WriteBarrierMode mode = new_table->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5407 
5408  DCHECK_LT(NumberOfElements(), new_table->Capacity());
5409 
5410  // Copy prefix to new array.
5411  for (int i = kPrefixStartIndex; i < kElementsStartIndex; i++) {
5412  new_table->set(i, get(i), mode);
5413  }
5414 
5415  // Rehash the elements.
5416  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5417  for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5418  uint32_t from_index = EntryToIndex(i);
5419  Tagged<Object> k = this->get(from_index);
5420  if (!IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
5421  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::HashForObject(roots, k);
5422  uint32_t insertion_index =
5423  EntryToIndex(new_table->FindInsertionEntry(cage_base, roots, hash));
5424  new_table->set_key(insertion_index, get(from_index), mode);
5425  for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5426  new_table->set(insertion_index + j, get(from_index + j), mode);
5427  }
5428  }
5429  new_table->SetNumberOfElements(NumberOfElements());
5430  new_table->SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5431 }
5432 
5433 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5434 InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::EntryForProbe(ReadOnlyRoots roots,
5435  Tagged<Object> k,
5436  int probe,
5437  InternalIndex expected) {
5438  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::HashForObject(roots, k);
5439  uint32_t capacity = this->Capacity();
5440  InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);
5441  for (int i = 1; i < probe; i++) {
5442  if (entry == expected) return expected;
5443  entry = NextProbe(entry, i, capacity);
5444  }
5445  return entry;
5446 }
5447 
5448 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5449 void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Swap(InternalIndex entry1, InternalIndex entry2,
5450  WriteBarrierMode mode) {
5451  int index1 = EntryToIndex(entry1);
5452  int index2 = EntryToIndex(entry2);
5453  Tagged<Object> temp[TodoShape::kEntrySize];
5454  Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
5455  for (int j = 0; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5456  temp[j] = get(index1 + j);
5457  }
5458  self->set_key(index1, get(index2), mode);
5459  for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5460  set(index1 + j, get(index2 + j), mode);
5461  }
5462  self->set_key(index2, temp[0], mode);
5463  for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5464  set(index2 + j, temp[j], mode);
5465  }
5466 }
5467 
5468 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5469 void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Rehash(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) {
5470  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5471  WriteBarrierMode mode = GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5472  ReadOnlyRoots roots = EarlyGetReadOnlyRoots();
5473  uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5474  bool done = false;
5475  for (int probe = 1; !done; probe++) {
5476  // All elements at entries given by one of the first _probe_ probes
5477  // are placed correctly. Other elements might need to be moved.
5478  done = true;
5479  for (InternalIndex current(0); current.raw_value() < capacity;
5480  /* {current} is advanced manually below, when appropriate.*/) {
5481  Tagged<Object> current_key = KeyAt(cage_base, current);
5482  if (!IsKey(roots, current_key)) {
5483  ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5484  continue;
5485  }
5486  InternalIndex target = EntryForProbe(roots, current_key, probe, current);
5487  if (current == target) {
5488  ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5489  continue;
5490  }
5491  Tagged<Object> target_key = KeyAt(cage_base, target);
5492  if (!IsKey(roots, target_key) ||
5493  EntryForProbe(roots, target_key, probe, target) != target) {
5494  // Put the current element into the correct position.
5495  Swap(current, target, mode);
5496  // The other element will be processed on the next iteration,
5497  // so don't advance {current} here!
5498  } else {
5499  // The place for the current element is occupied. Leave the element
5500  // for the next probe.
5501  done = false;
5502  ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5503  }
5504  }
5505  }
5506  // Wipe deleted entries.
5507  Tagged<Object> the_hole = roots.the_hole_value();
5508  Tagged<HeapObject> undefined = roots.undefined_value();
5509  Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
5510  for (InternalIndex current : InternalIndex::Range(capacity)) {
5511  if (KeyAt(cage_base, current) == the_hole) {
5512  self->set_key(EntryToIndex(current) + kEntryKeyIndex, undefined,
5513  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5514  }
5515  }
5516  SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5517 }
5518 
5519 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5520 template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType>
5521  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5522 HandleType<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::EnsureCapacity(
5523  IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> table, int n,
5524  AllocationType allocation) {
5525  if (table->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(n)) return table;
5526 
5527  int capacity = table->Capacity();
5528  int new_nof = table->NumberOfElements() + n;
5529 
5530  bool should_pretenure = allocation == AllocationType::kOld ||
5531  ((capacity > kMinCapacityForPretenure) &&
5532  !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*table));
5533  HandleType<Derived> new_table = HashTable::New(
5534  isolate, new_nof,
5535  should_pretenure ? AllocationType::kOld : AllocationType::kYoung);
5536 
5537  table->Rehash(isolate, *new_table);
5538  return new_table;
5539 }
5540 
5541 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5542 bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(
5543  int number_of_additional_elements) {
5544  return HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(Capacity(), NumberOfElements(),
5545  NumberOfDeletedElements(),
5546  number_of_additional_elements);
5547 }
5548 
5549 // static
5550 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5551 bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(
5552  int capacity, int number_of_elements, int number_of_deleted_elements,
5553  int number_of_additional_elements) {
5554  int nof = number_of_elements + number_of_additional_elements;
5555  // Return true if:
5556  // 50% is still free after adding number_of_additional_elements elements and
5557  // at most 50% of the free elements are deleted elements.
5558  if ((nof < capacity) &&
5559  ((number_of_deleted_elements <= (capacity - nof) / 2))) {
5560  int needed_free = nof / 2;
5561  if (nof + needed_free <= capacity) return true;
5562  }
5563  return false;
5564 }
5565 
5566 // static
5567 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5568 uint32_t HashTable<Derived, Shape>::ComputeCapacityWithShrink(
5569  uint32_t current_capacity, uint32_t at_least_room_for) {
5570  // Shrink to fit the number of elements if only a quarter of the
5571  // capacity is filled with elements.
5572  if (at_least_room_for > (current_capacity / 4)) return current_capacity;
5573  // Recalculate the smaller capacity actually needed.
5574  uint32_t new_capacity = ComputeCapacity(at_least_room_for);
5575  DCHECK_GE(new_capacity, at_least_room_for);
5576  // Don't go lower than room for {kMinShrinkCapacity} elements.
5577  if (new_capacity < Derived::kMinShrinkCapacity) return current_capacity;
5578  return new_capacity;
5579 }
5580 
5581 // static
5582 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5583 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5584  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5585 HandleType<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Shrink(Isolate* isolate,
5586  HandleType<Derived> table,
5587  int additional_capacity) {
5588  uint32_t new_capacity = ComputeCapacityWithShrink(
5589  table->Capacity(), table->NumberOfElements() + additional_capacity);
5590  if (new_capacity == table->Capacity()) return table;
5591  DCHECK_GE(new_capacity, Derived::kMinShrinkCapacity);
5592 
5593  bool pretenure = (new_capacity > kMinCapacityForPretenure) &&
5594  !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*table);
5595  HandleType<Derived> new_table =
5596  HashTable::New(isolate, new_capacity,
5597  pretenure ? AllocationType::kOld : AllocationType::kYoung,
5598  USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY);
5599 
5600  table->Rehash(isolate, *new_table);
5601  return new_table;
5602 }
5603 
5604 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5605 InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::FindInsertionEntry(
5606  PtrComprCageBase cage_base, ReadOnlyRoots roots, uint32_t hash) {
5607  uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5608  uint32_t count = 1;
5609  // EnsureCapacity will guarantee the hash table is never full.
5610  for (InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);;
5611  entry = NextProbe(entry, count++, capacity)) {
5612  if (!IsKey(roots, KeyAt(cage_base, entry))) return entry;
5613  }
5614 }
5615 
5616 std::optional<Tagged<PropertyCell>>
5617 GlobalDictionary::TryFindPropertyCellForConcurrentLookupIterator(
5618  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name, RelaxedLoadTag tag) {
5619  // This reimplements HashTable::FindEntry for use in a concurrent setting.
5620  // 1) Atomic loads.
5621  // 2) IsPendingAllocation checks.
5622  // 3) Return the PropertyCell value instead of the InternalIndex to avoid a
5623  // repeated load (unsafe with concurrent modifications).
5624 
5625  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5626  PtrComprCageBase cage_base{isolate};
5627  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5628  const int32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, name);
5629  const uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5630  uint32_t count = 1;
5631  Tagged<Object> undefined = roots.undefined_value();
5632  Tagged<Object> the_hole = roots.the_hole_value();
5633  // EnsureCapacity will guarantee the hash table is never full.
5634  for (InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);;
5635  entry = NextProbe(entry, count++, capacity)) {
5636  Tagged<Object> element = KeyAt(cage_base, entry, kRelaxedLoad);
5637  if (isolate->heap()->IsPendingAllocation(element)) return {};
5638  if (element == undefined) return {};
5639  if (TodoShape::kMatchNeedsHoleCheck && element == the_hole) continue;
5640  if (!TodoShape::IsMatch(name, element)) continue;
5641  CHECK(IsPropertyCell(element, cage_base));
5642  return Cast<PropertyCell>(element);
5643  }
5644 }
5645 
5646 Handle<StringSet> StringSet::New(Isolate* isolate) {
5647  return HashTable::New(isolate, 0);
5648 }
5649 
5650 Handle<StringSet> StringSet::Add(Isolate* isolate, Handle<StringSet> stringset,
5651  DirectHandle<String> name) {
5652  if (!stringset->Has(isolate, name)) {
5653  stringset = EnsureCapacity(isolate, stringset);
5654  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), *name);
5655  InternalIndex entry = stringset->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
5656  stringset->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *name);
5657  stringset->ElementAdded();
5658  }
5659  return stringset;
5660 }
5661 
5662 bool StringSet::Has(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name) {
5663  return FindEntry(isolate, *name).is_found();
5664 }

5666 Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> RegisteredSymbolTable::Add(
5667  Isolate* isolate, Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> table,
5668  DirectHandle<String> key, DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol) {
5669  // Validate that the key is absent.
5670  SLOW_DCHECK(table->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5671 
5672  table = EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
5673  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), key);
5674  InternalIndex entry = table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
5675  table->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
5676  table->set(EntryToValueIndex(entry), *symbol);
5677  table->ElementAdded();
5678  return table;
5679 }

5706 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5707 int BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::NextEnumerationIndex(
5708  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary) {
5709  int index = dictionary->next_enumeration_index();
5710  // Check whether the next enumeration index is valid.
5711  if (!PropertyDetails::IsValidIndex(index)) {
5712  // If not, we generate new indices for the properties.
5713  DirectHandle<FixedArray> iteration_order =
5714  IterationIndices(isolate, dictionary);
5715  int length = iteration_order->length();
5716  DCHECK_LE(length, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5717 
5718  // Iterate over the dictionary using the enumeration order and update
5719  // the dictionary with new enumeration indices.
5720  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5721  InternalIndex internal_index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
5722  DCHECK(dictionary->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(),
5723  dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, internal_index)));
5724 
5725  int enum_index = PropertyDetails::kInitialIndex + i;
5726 
5727  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(internal_index);
5728  PropertyDetails new_details = details.set_index(enum_index);
5729  dictionary->DetailsAtPut(internal_index, new_details);
5730  }
5731 
5732  index = PropertyDetails::kInitialIndex + length;
5733  }
5734 
5735  // Don't update the next enumeration index here, since we might be looking at
5736  // an immutable empty dictionary.
5737  return index;
5738 }
5739 
5740 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5741 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5742  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5743 HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::DeleteEntry(
5744  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, InternalIndex entry) {
5745  DCHECK(TodoShape::kEntrySize != 3 ||
5746  dictionary->DetailsAt(entry).IsConfigurable());
5747  dictionary->ClearEntry(entry);
5748  dictionary->ElementRemoved();
5749  return Shrink(isolate, dictionary);
5750 }

5752 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5753 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5754  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5755 HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::AtPut(
5756  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5757  DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
5758  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key);
5759 
5760  // If the entry is present set the value;
5761  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5762  return Derived::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5763  }
5764 
5765  // We don't need to copy over the enumeration index.
5766  dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
5767  if (TodoShape::kEntrySize == 3) dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
5768  return dictionary;
5769 }

5771 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5772 void Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::UncheckedAtPut(
5773  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5774  DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
5775  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key);
5776 
5777  // If the entry is present set the value;
5778  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5779  Derived::UncheckedAdd(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5780  } else {
5781  // We don't need to copy over the enumeration index.
5782  dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
5783  if (TodoShape::kEntrySize == 3) dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
5784  }
5785 }

5787 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5788 template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType>
5789  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5790 HandleType<Derived>
5791 BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::AddNoUpdateNextEnumerationIndex(
5792  IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5793  DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5794  InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5795  // Insert element at empty or deleted entry.
5796  return Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value,
5797  details, entry_out);
5798 }

5800 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5801 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5802  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5803 HandleType<Derived> BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(
5804  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5805  DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5806  InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5807  // Insert element at empty or deleted entry
5808  DCHECK_EQ(0, details.dictionary_index());
5809  // Assign an enumeration index to the property and update
5810  // SetNextEnumerationIndex.
5811  int index = Derived::NextEnumerationIndex(isolate, dictionary);
5812  details = details.set_index(index);
5813  dictionary = AddNoUpdateNextEnumerationIndex(isolate, dictionary, key, value,
5814  details, entry_out);
5815  // Update enumeration index here in order to avoid potential modification of
5816  // the canonical empty dictionary which lives in read only space.
5817  dictionary->set_next_enumeration_index(index + 1);
5818  return dictionary;
5819 }

5821 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5822 template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType,
5823  AllocationType key_allocation>
5824  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5825 HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(
5826  IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5827  DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5828  InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5829  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5830  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, key);
5831  // Validate that the key is absent.
5832  SLOW_DCHECK(dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5833  // Check whether the dictionary should be extended.
5834  dictionary = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, dictionary);
5835 
5836  // Compute the key object.
5837  DirectHandle<Object> k =
5838  TodoShape::template AsHandle<key_allocation>(isolate, key);
5839 
5840  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, roots, hash);
5841  dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *k, *value, details);
5842  DCHECK(IsNumber(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry)) ||
5843  IsUniqueName(TodoShape::Unwrap(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry))));
5844  dictionary->ElementAdded();
5845  if (entry_out) *entry_out = entry;
5846  return dictionary;
5847 }

5849 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5850 template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType,
5851  AllocationType key_allocation>
5852  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5853 void Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::UncheckedAdd(IsolateT* isolate,
5854  HandleType<Derived> dictionary,
5855  Key key,
5856  DirectHandle<Object> value,
5857  PropertyDetails details) {
5858  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5859  uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, key);
5860  // Validate that the key is absent and we capacity is sufficient.
5861  SLOW_DCHECK(dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5862  DCHECK(dictionary->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(1));
5863 
5864  // Compute the key object.
5865  DirectHandle<Object> k =
5866  TodoShape::template AsHandle<key_allocation>(isolate, key);
5867 
5868  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, roots, hash);
5869  dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *k, *value, details);
5870  DCHECK(IsNumber(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry)) ||
5871  IsUniqueName(TodoShape::Unwrap(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry))));
5872 }

5895 
5896 void NumberDictionary::UpdateMaxNumberKey(
5897  uint32_t key, DirectHandle<JSObject> dictionary_holder) {
5898  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5899  // If the dictionary requires slow elements an element has already
5900  // been added at a high index.
5901  if (requires_slow_elements()) return;
5902  // Check if this index is high enough that we should require slow
5903  // elements.
5904  if (key > kRequiresSlowElementsLimit) {
5905  if (!dictionary_holder.is_null()) {
5906  dictionary_holder->RequireSlowElements(this);
5907  }
5908  set_requires_slow_elements();
5909  return;
5910  }
5911  // Update max key value.
5912  Tagged<Object> max_index_object = get(kMaxNumberKeyIndex);
5913  if (!IsSmi(max_index_object) || max_number_key() < key) {
5914  FixedArray::set(kMaxNumberKeyIndex,
5915  Smi::FromInt(key << kRequiresSlowElementsTagSize));
5916  }
5917 }

5919 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5920  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<NumberDictionary>,
5921  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary>>)
5922 HandleType<NumberDictionary> NumberDictionary::Set(
5923  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<NumberDictionary> dictionary, uint32_t key,
5924  DirectHandle<Object> value, DirectHandle<JSObject> dictionary_holder,
5925  PropertyDetails details) {
5926  // We could call Set with empty dictionaries. UpdateMaxNumberKey doesn't
5927  // expect empty dictionaries so make sure to call AtPut that correctly handles
5928  // them by creating new dictionary when required.
5929  HandleType<NumberDictionary> new_dictionary =
5930  AtPut(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5931  new_dictionary->UpdateMaxNumberKey(key, dictionary_holder);
5932  return new_dictionary;
5933 }

5951 void NumberDictionary::CopyValuesTo(Tagged<FixedArray> elements) {
5952  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5953  int pos = 0;
5954  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5955  WriteBarrierMode mode = elements->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5956  for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5957  Tagged<Object> k;
5958  if (this->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) {
5959  elements->set(pos++, this->ValueAt(i), mode);
5960  }
5961  }
5962  DCHECK_EQ(pos, elements->length());
5963 }

5965 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5966 int Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::NumberOfEnumerableProperties() {
5967  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5968  int result = 0;
5969  for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5970  Tagged<Object> k;
5971  if (!this->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
5972  if (Object::FilterKey(k, ENUMERABLE_STRINGS)) continue;
5973  PropertyDetails details = this->DetailsAt(i);
5974  PropertyAttributes attr = details.attributes();
5975  if ((int{attr} & ONLY_ENUMERABLE) == 0) result++;
5976  }
5977  return result;
5978 }
5979 
5980 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5981 DirectHandle<FixedArray> BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::IterationIndices(
5982  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary) {
5983  DirectHandle<FixedArray> array =
5984  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5985  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5986  int array_size = 0;
5987  {
5988  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5989  Tagged<Derived> raw_dictionary = *dictionary;
5990  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
5991  Tagged<Object> k;
5992  if (!raw_dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
5993  array->set(array_size++, Smi::FromInt(i.as_int()));
5994  }
5995 
5996  // The global dictionary doesn't track its deletion count, so we may iterate
5997  // fewer entries than the count of elements claimed by the dictionary.
5998  if (std::is_same_v<Derived, GlobalDictionary>) {
5999  DCHECK_LE(array_size, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
6000  } else {
6001  DCHECK_EQ(array_size, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
6002  }
6003 
6004  EnumIndexComparator<Derived> cmp(raw_dictionary);
6005  // Use AtomicSlot wrapper to ensure that std::sort uses atomic load and
6006  // store operations that are safe for concurrent marking.
6007  AtomicSlot start(array->RawFieldOfFirstElement());
6008  std::sort(start, start + array_size, cmp);
6009  }
6010  return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, array, array_size);
6011 }
6012 
6013 // Backwards lookup (slow).
6014 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6015 Tagged<Object> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::SlowReverseLookup(
6016  Tagged<Object> value) {
6017  Tagged<Derived> dictionary = Cast<Derived>(this);
6018  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6019  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
6020  Tagged<Object> k;
6021  if (!dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
6022  Tagged<Object> e = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
6023  if (e == value) return k;
6024  }
6025  return roots.undefined_value();
6026 }

6028 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6029 void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::FillEntriesWithHoles(
6030  DirectHandle<Derived> table) {
6031  auto roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6032  int length = table->length();
6033  for (int i = Derived::EntryToIndex(InternalIndex(0)); i < length; i++) {
6034  table->set_the_hole(roots, i);
6035  }
6036 }

6038 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6039 Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
6040  PtrComprCageBase cage_base, DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
6041  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6042  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6043  DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
6044 
6045  InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, hash);
6046  if (entry.is_not_found()) return roots.the_hole_value();
6047  return this->get(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry) + 1);
6048 }

6050 // The implementation should be in sync with
6051 // CodeStubAssembler::NameToIndexHashTableLookup.
6052 int NameToIndexHashTable::Lookup(Tagged<Name> key) {
6053  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6054  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(this);
6055  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6056 
6057  InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, key->hash());
6058  if (entry.is_not_found()) return -1;
6059  return Cast<Smi>(this->get(EntryToValueIndex(entry))).value();
6060 }

6062 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6063 Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
6064  DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6065  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6066 
6067  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(this);
6068  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6069  DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
6070 
6071  // If the object does not have an identity hash, it was never used as a key.
6072  Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(*key);
6073  if (IsUndefined(hash, roots)) {
6074  return roots.the_hole_value();
6075  }
6076  return Lookup(cage_base, key, Smi::ToInt(hash));
6077 }

6080 Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
6081  DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
6082  return Lookup(GetPtrComprCageBase(this), key, hash);
6083 }

6099 int NameToIndexHashTable::IndexAt(InternalIndex entry) {
6100  Tagged<Object> value = ValueAt(entry);
6101  if (IsSmi(value)) {
6102  int index = Smi::ToInt(value);
6103  DCHECK_LE(0, index);
6104  return index;

6109 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6110 Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(
6111  Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6112  DirectHandle<Object> value) {
6113  Isolate* isolate = Heap::FromWritableHeapObject(*table)->isolate();
6114  DCHECK(table->IsKey(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), *key));
6115  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate)));
6116 
6117  // Make sure the key object has an identity hash code.
6118  int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6119 
6120  return ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(isolate, table, key, value,
6121  hash);
6122 }

6124 namespace {
6125 
6126 template <typename T, template <typename> typename HandleType>
6127 void RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(Isolate* isolate, HandleType<T> table) {
6128  // Rehash if more than 33% of the entries are deleted entries.
6129  // TODO(verwaest): Consider to shrink the fixed array in place.
6130  if ((table->NumberOfDeletedElements() << 1) > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6131  table->Rehash(isolate);
6132  }
6133  // If we're out of luck, we didn't get a GC recently, and so rehashing
6134  // isn't enough to avoid a crash.
6135  if (!table->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(1)) {
6136  uint32_t nof = table->NumberOfElements() + 1;
6137  uint32_t capacity = T::ComputeCapacity(nof);
6138  if (capacity > T::kMaxCapacity) {
6139  for (size_t i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
6140  isolate->heap()->CollectAllGarbage(
6141  GCFlag::kNoFlags, GarbageCollectionReason::kFullHashtable);
6142  }
6143  table->Rehash(isolate);
6144  }
6145  }
6146 }
6147 
6148 } // namespace
6149 
6150 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6151 Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(
6152  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6153  DirectHandle<Object> value, int32_t hash) {
6154  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
6155  DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6156  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, roots));
6157 
6158  InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6159 
6160  // Key is already in table, just overwrite value.
6161  if (entry.is_found()) {
6162  table->set(Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry), *value);
6163  return table;
6164  }
6165 
6166  RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(isolate, table);
6167 
6168  // Check whether the hash table should be extended.
6169  table = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
6170  table->AddEntry(table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash), *key, *value);
6171  return table;
6172 }
6173 
6174 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6175 Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Remove(
6176  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6177  bool* was_present) {
6178  DCHECK(table->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), *key));
6179 
6180  Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(*key);
6181  if (IsUndefined(hash)) {
6182  *was_present = false;
6183  return table;
6184  }
6185 
6186  return Remove(isolate, table, key, was_present, Smi::ToInt(hash));
6187 }
6188 
6189 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6190 Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Remove(
6191  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6192  bool* was_present, int32_t hash) {
6193  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6194  DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6195 
6196  InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6197  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6198  *was_present = false;
6199  return table;
6200  }
6201 
6202  *was_present = true;
6203  table->RemoveEntry(entry);
6204  return Derived::Shrink(isolate, table);
6205 }
6206 
6207 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6208 void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::AddEntry(InternalIndex entry,
6209  Tagged<Object> key,
6210  Tagged<Object> value) {
6211  Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
6212  self->set_key(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry), key);
6213  self->set(Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry), value);
6214  self->ElementAdded();
6215 }
6216 
6217 template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6218 void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::RemoveEntry(InternalIndex entry) {
6219  auto roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6220  this->set_the_hole(roots, Derived::EntryToIndex(entry));
6221  this->set_the_hole(roots, Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry));
6222  this->ElementRemoved();
6223 }
6224 
6225 template <typename Derived, int N>
6226 std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Lookup(
6227  DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6228  return Lookup(GetPtrComprCageBase(this), key);
6229 }
6230 
6231 template <typename Derived, int N>
6232 std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Lookup(
6233  PtrComprCageBase cage_base, DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6234  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6235 
6236  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6237  DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
6238 
6239  Tagged<Object> hash_obj = Object::GetHash(*key);
6240  if (IsUndefined(hash_obj, roots)) {
6241  return {roots.the_hole_value(), roots.the_hole_value()};
6242  }
6243  int32_t hash = Smi::ToInt(hash_obj);
6244 
6245  InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, hash);
6246  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6247  return {roots.the_hole_value(), roots.the_hole_value()};
6248  }
6249 
6250  int start_index = this->EntryToIndex(entry) +
6251  ObjectMultiHashTableShape<N>::kEntryValueIndex;
6252  std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> values;
6253  for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
6254  values[i] = this->get(start_index + i);
6255  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(values[i]));
6256  }
6257  return values;
6258 }
6259 
6260 // static
6261 template <typename Derived, int N>
6262 Handle<Derived> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Put(
6263  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6264  const std::array<DirectHandle<Object>, N>& values) {
6265  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
6266  DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6267 
6268  int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6269  InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6270 
6271  // Overwrite values if entry is found.
6272  if (entry.is_found()) {
6273  table->SetEntryValues(entry, values);
6274  return table;
6275  }
6276 
6277  RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(isolate, table);
6278 
6279  // Check whether the hash table should be extended.
6280  table = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
6281  entry = table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
6282  table->set(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
6283  table->SetEntryValues(entry, values);
6284  return table;
6285 }
6286 
6287 template <typename Derived, int N>
6288 void ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::SetEntryValues(
6289  InternalIndex entry, const std::array<DirectHandle<Object>, N>& values) {
6290  int start_index = EntryToValueIndexStart(entry);
6291  for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
6292  this->set(start_index + i, *values[i]);
6293  }
6294 }

6296 Handle<ObjectHashSet> ObjectHashSet::Add(Isolate* isolate,
6297  Handle<ObjectHashSet> set,
6298  DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6299  int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6300  if (!set->Has(isolate, key, hash)) {
6301  set = EnsureCapacity(isolate, set);
6302  InternalIndex entry = set->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
6303  set->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
6304  set->ElementAdded();
6305  }
6306  return set;
6307 }

6351 void JSWeakCollection::Set(DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> weak_collection,
6352  DirectHandle<Object> key, DirectHandle<Object> value,
6353  int32_t hash) {

6356  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(weak_collection->table()), Isolate::Current());

6359  EphemeronHashTable::Put(Isolate::Current(), table, key, value, hash);
6360  weak_collection->set_table(*new_table);
6361  if (*table != *new_table) {

6363  EphemeronHashTable::FillEntriesWithHoles(table);
6364  }

6367 bool JSWeakCollection::Delete(DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> weak_collection,
6368  DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
6369  DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*key) || IsSymbol(*key));
6370  Handle<EphemeronHashTable> table(
6371  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(weak_collection->table()), Isolate::Current());
6372  DCHECK(table->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), *key));
6373  bool was_present = false;
6374  DirectHandle<EphemeronHashTable> new_table = EphemeronHashTable::Remove(
6375  Isolate::Current(), table, key, &was_present, hash);
6376  weak_collection->set_table(*new_table);
6377  if (*table != *new_table) {
6378  // Zap the old table since we didn't record slots for its elements.
6379  EphemeronHashTable::FillEntriesWithHoles(table);
6380  }

6383 
6384 DirectHandle<JSArray> JSWeakCollection::GetEntries(
6385  DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> holder, uint32_t max_entries) {
6386  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
6387  DirectHandle<EphemeronHashTable> table(
6388  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(holder->table()), isolate);
6389  if (max_entries == 0 || max_entries > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6390  max_entries = table->NumberOfElements();
6391  }
6392  int values_per_entry = IsJSWeakMap(*holder) ? 2 : 1;
6393  DirectHandle<FixedArray> entries =
6394  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(max_entries * values_per_entry);
6395  // Recompute max_values because GC could have removed elements from the table.
6396  if (max_entries > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6397  max_entries = table->NumberOfElements();
6398  }
6399 
6400  {
6401  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6402  ReadOnlyRoots roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate);
6403  uint32_t count = 0;
6404  for (uint32_t i = 0;
6405  count / values_per_entry < max_entries && i < table->Capacity(); i++) {
6406  Tagged<Object> key;
6407  if (table->ToKey(roots, InternalIndex(i), &key)) {
6408  entries->set(count++, key);
6409  if (values_per_entry > 1) {
6410  Tagged<Object> value = table->Lookup(direct_handle(key, isolate));
6411  entries->set(count++, value);
6412  }
6413  }
6414  }
6415  DCHECK_EQ(max_entries * values_per_entry, count);
6416  }
6417  return isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(entries);
6418 }

6420 void JSDisposableStackBase::InitializeJSDisposableStackBase(
6421  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSDisposableStackBase> disposable_stack) {
6422  DirectHandle<FixedArray> array = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(0);
6423  disposable_stack->set_stack(*array);

6425  disposable_stack->set_has_awaited(false);
6426  disposable_stack->set_suppressed_error_created(false);
6427  disposable_stack->set_length(0);
6428  disposable_stack->set_state(DisposableStackState::kPending);
6429  disposable_stack->set_error(*(isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value()));
6430  disposable_stack->set_error_message(
6431  *(isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value()));
6432 }

6443 // static
6444 Handle<PropertyCell> PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(
6445  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
6446  InternalIndex entry, PropertyDetails new_details,
6447  DirectHandle<Object> new_value) {

6450  DCHECK(cell->property_details().IsConfigurable());
6451  DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(cell->value(), isolate));
6452

6454  Handle<PropertyCell> new_cell =
6455  isolate->factory()->NewPropertyCell(name, new_details, new_value);
6456  dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *new_cell);

6462 static bool RemainsConstantType(Tagged<PropertyCell> cell,
6463  Tagged<Object> value) {
6464  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6465  // TODO(dcarney): double->smi and smi->double transition from kConstant
6466  if (IsSmi(cell->value()) && IsSmi(value)) {
6467  return true;
6468  } else if (IsHeapObject(cell->value()) && IsHeapObject(value)) {
6469  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<HeapObject>(value)->map();
6470  return Cast<HeapObject>(cell->value())->map() == map && map->is_stable();
6471  }
6472  return false;
6473 }

6475 // static
6476 PropertyCellType PropertyCell::InitialType(Isolate* isolate,
6477  Tagged<Object> value) {
6478  return IsUndefined(value, isolate) ? PropertyCellType::kUndefined
6479  : PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6480 }
6481 
6482 // static
6483 PropertyCellType PropertyCell::UpdatedType(Isolate* isolate,
6484  Tagged<PropertyCell> cell,
6485  Tagged<Object> value,
6486  PropertyDetails details) {
6487  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6488  DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(value, isolate));
6489  DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(cell->value(), isolate));
6490  switch (details.cell_type()) {
6491  case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
6492  return PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6493  case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
6494  if (value == cell->value()) return PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6495  [[fallthrough]];
6496  case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
6497  if (RemainsConstantType(cell, value)) {
6498  return PropertyCellType::kConstantType;
6499  }
6500  [[fallthrough]];
6501  case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
6502  return PropertyCellType::kMutable;
6503  case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
6504  UNREACHABLE();
6505  }
6506  UNREACHABLE();
6507 }
6508 
6509 Handle<PropertyCell> PropertyCell::PrepareForAndSetValue(
6510  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
6511  InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
6512  DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(*value, isolate));
6513  Tagged<PropertyCell> raw_cell = dictionary->CellAt(entry);
6514  CHECK(!IsAnyHole(raw_cell->value(), isolate));
6515  const PropertyDetails original_details = raw_cell->property_details();
6516  // Data accesses could be cached in ics or optimized code.
6517  bool invalidate = original_details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
6518  details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor;
6519  int index = original_details.dictionary_index();
6520  DCHECK_LT(0, index);
6521  details = details.set_index(index);
6522 
6523  PropertyCellType new_type =
6524  UpdatedType(isolate, raw_cell, *value, original_details);
6525  details = details.set_cell_type(new_type);
6526 
6527  Handle<PropertyCell> cell(raw_cell, isolate);
6528 
6529  if (invalidate) {
6530  cell = PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry,
6531  details, value);
6532  } else {
6533  cell->Transition(details, value);
6534  // Deopt when transitioning from a constant type or when making a writable
6535  // property read-only. Making a read-only property writable again is not
6536  // interesting because Turbofan does not currently rely on read-only unless
6537  // the property is also configurable, in which case it will stay read-only
6538  // forever.
6539  if (original_details.cell_type() != new_type ||
6540  (!original_details.IsReadOnly() && details.IsReadOnly())) {
6541  DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
6542  isolate, *cell, DependentCode::kPropertyCellChangedGroup);
6543  }
6544  }
6545  return cell;
6546 }

6548 // static
6549 void PropertyCell::InvalidateProtector(Isolate* isolate) {
6550  if (value() != Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorInvalid)) {
6551  DCHECK_EQ(value(), Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorValid));
6552  set_value(Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorInvalid), kReleaseStore,
6553  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
6554  DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
6555  isolate, *this, DependentCode::kPropertyCellChangedGroup);
6556  }
6557 }
