6559 // static
6560 bool PropertyCell::CheckDataIsCompatible(PropertyDetails details,
6561  Tagged<Object> value) {
6562  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6563  PropertyCellType cell_type = details.cell_type();
6564  CHECK_NE(cell_type, PropertyCellType::kInTransition);
6565  if (IsPropertyCellHole(value)) {
6566  CHECK_EQ(cell_type, PropertyCellType::kConstant);
6567  } else {
6568  CHECK_EQ(IsAccessorInfo(value) || IsAccessorPair(value),
6569  details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor);
6570  DCHECK_IMPLIES(cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined,
6571  IsUndefined(value));
6572  }
6573  return true;
6574 }

6576 #ifdef DEBUG
6577 bool PropertyCell::CanTransitionTo(PropertyDetails new_details,
6578  Tagged<Object> new_value) const {
6579  // Extending the implementation of PropertyCells with additional states
6580  // and/or transitions likely requires changes to PropertyCellData::Serialize.
6581  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6582  DCHECK(CheckDataIsCompatible(new_details, new_value));
6583  switch (property_details().cell_type()) {
6584  case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
6585  return new_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined;
6586  case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
6587  return !IsPropertyCellHole(value()) &&
6588  new_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined;
6589  case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
6590  return new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstantType ||
6591  new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
6592  (new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
6593  IsPropertyCellHole(new_value));
6594  case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
6595  return new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
6596  (new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
6597  IsPropertyCellHole(new_value));
6598  case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
6599  UNREACHABLE();
6600  }
6601  UNREACHABLE();
6602 }
6603 #endif // DEBUG

6605 int JSGeneratorObject::code_offset() const {
6606  DCHECK(IsSmi(input_or_debug_pos()));
6607  int code_offset = Smi::ToInt(input_or_debug_pos());
6608 
6609  // The stored bytecode offset is relative to a different base than what
6610  // is used in the source position table, hence the subtraction.
6611  code_offset -= BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag;
6612  return code_offset;
6613 }

6628 // static
6629 Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> AccessCheckInfo::Get(Isolate* isolate,
6630  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
6631  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6632  DCHECK(receiver->map()->is_access_check_needed());
6633  Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = receiver->map()->GetConstructor();
6634  if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(maybe_constructor)) {
6635  Tagged<Object> data_obj =
6636  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(maybe_constructor)->GetAccessCheckInfo();
6637  if (IsUndefined(data_obj, isolate)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6638  return Cast<AccessCheckInfo>(data_obj);
6639  }
6640  // Might happen for a detached context.
6641  if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6642  Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
6643  // Might happen for the debug context.
6644  if (!constructor->shared()->IsApiFunction()) return AccessCheckInfo();
6645 
6646  Tagged<Object> data_obj =
6647  constructor->shared()->api_func_data()->GetAccessCheckInfo();
6648  if (IsUndefined(data_obj, isolate)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6649 
6650  return Cast<AccessCheckInfo>(data_obj);
6651 }
6652 
6653 Address Smi::LexicographicCompare(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Smi> x,
6654  Tagged<Smi> y) {
6655  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6656  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
6657 
6658  int x_value = Smi::ToInt(x);
6659  int y_value = Smi::ToInt(y);
6660 
6661  // If the integers are equal so are the string representations.
6662  if (x_value == y_value) return Smi::FromInt(0).ptr();
6663 
6664  // If one of the integers is zero the normal integer order is the
6665  // same as the lexicographic order of the string representations.
6666  if (x_value == 0 || y_value == 0) {
6667  return Smi::FromInt(x_value < y_value ? -1 : 1).ptr();
6668  }
6669 
6670  // If only one of the integers is negative the negative number is
6671  // smallest because the char code of '-' is less than the char code
6672  // of any digit. Otherwise, we make both values positive.
6673 
6674  // Use unsigned values otherwise the logic is incorrect for -MIN_INT on
6675  // architectures using 32-bit Smis.
6676  uint32_t x_scaled = x_value;
6677  uint32_t y_scaled = y_value;
6678  if (x_value < 0) {
6679  if (y_value >= 0) {
6680  return Smi::FromInt(-1).ptr();
6681  } else {
6682  y_scaled = base::NegateWithWraparound(y_value);
6683  }
6684  x_scaled = base::NegateWithWraparound(x_value);
6685  } else if (y_value < 0) {
6686  return Smi::FromInt(1).ptr();
6687  }
6688 
6689  // clang-format off
6690  static const uint32_t kPowersOf10[] = {
6691  1, 10, 100, 1000,
6692  10 * 1000, 100 * 1000, 1000 * 1000, 10 * 1000 * 1000,
6693  100 * 1000 * 1000, 1000 * 1000 * 1000};
6694  // clang-format on
6695 
6696  // If the integers have the same number of decimal digits they can be
6697  // compared directly as the numeric order is the same as the
6698  // lexicographic order. If one integer has fewer digits, it is scaled
6699  // by some power of 10 to have the same number of digits as the longer
6700  // integer. If the scaled integers are equal it means the shorter
6701  // integer comes first in the lexicographic order.
6702 
6703  // From http://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#IntegerLog10
6704  int x_log2 = 31 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(x_scaled);
6705  int x_log10 = ((x_log2 + 1) * 1233) >> 12;
6706  x_log10 -= x_scaled < kPowersOf10[x_log10];
6707 
6708  int y_log2 = 31 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(y_scaled);
6709  int y_log10 = ((y_log2 + 1) * 1233) >> 12;
6710  y_log10 -= y_scaled < kPowersOf10[y_log10];
6711 
6712  int tie = 0;
6713 
6714  if (x_log10 < y_log10) {
6715  // X has fewer digits. We would like to simply scale up X but that
6716  // might overflow, e.g when comparing 9 with 1_000_000_000, 9 would
6717  // be scaled up to 9_000_000_000. So we scale up by the next
6718  // smallest power and scale down Y to drop one digit. It is OK to
6719  // drop one digit from the longer integer since the final digit is
6720  // past the length of the shorter integer.
6721  x_scaled *= kPowersOf10[y_log10 - x_log10 - 1];
6722  y_scaled /= 10;
6723  tie = -1;
6724  } else if (y_log10 < x_log10) {
6725  y_scaled *= kPowersOf10[x_log10 - y_log10 - 1];
6726  x_scaled /= 10;
6727  tie = 1;
6728  }
6729 
6730  if (x_scaled < y_scaled) return Smi::FromInt(-1).ptr();
6731  if (x_scaled > y_scaled) return Smi::FromInt(1).ptr();
6732  return Smi::FromInt(tie).ptr();
6733 }
6734 
6735 // static
6736 bool MapWord::IsMapOrForwarded(Tagged<Map> map) {
6737  MapWord map_word = map->map_word(kRelaxedLoad);
6738  if (map_word.IsForwardingAddress()) {
6739  // During GC we can't access forwarded maps without synchronization.
6740  return true;
6741  }
6742  // The meta map might be moved away by GC too but we can read instance
6743  // type from both old and new location as it can't change.
6744  return InstanceTypeChecker::IsMap(map_word.ToMap()->instance_type());
6745 }
